{"type":"message","id":"fe3ebace","parentId":"34b9f9c6","timestamp":"2026-03-05T09:02:13.689Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_6e333456a6e74644bb1c0328","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Task: Error Spike Investigation\n\n**Priority:** HIGH\n**Created:** 2026-03-05 02:03 AM\n**Agent:** ogedei\n**Status:** RESOLVED (investigated by Kublai during reflection)\n\n## Resolution\n\n**ROOT CAUSE:** The \"117 errors/5m\" are log noise, not operational failures.\n\nThe tick/tock system counts ERROR-level log entries, but OpenClaw's code logs many informational messages at ERROR level:\n- \"Service unit not found\" — normal on macOS\n- \"Service not installed. Run: openclaw gateway install\" — informational\n- \"Other gateway-like services detected\" — informational\n- \"Cleanup hint: launchctl bootout...\" — informational\n\n**VERDICT:** System is HEALTHY. The \"degraded\" status is a false alarm caused by miscalibrated tick threshold.\n\n## Action Required\n\nTemujin needs to fix the tick threshold to filter out these informational ERROR-level messages.\n\n## Original Context\n\nSystem has been in DEGRADED status since ~01:13 AM:\n- Current: 117 errors/5m, 261 errors/1h, 1071 trend\n- All services report UP (neo4j=up, redis=up)\n- error_clusters field is EMPTY in tock output\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772701333688}}
