{"type":"message","id":"832f5949","parentId":"e1595012","timestamp":"2026-03-05T09:20:32.953Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - none of the other Kurultai agents have active sessions right now. Only my session (agent:main:main) is active.\n\nSo we have a HIGH priority task for Temujin (\"Build Vision A of Parse for Agents\") that:\n1. Is PENDING\n2. Has a deadline of \"ASAP - Danny wants this completed and testable\"\n3. Was created 2+ hours ago\n4. Temujin has no active session and no `.executing` file\n\nThis is a task that needs attention. According to HEARTBEAT.md:\n- \"If Something Needs Attention: Report: 1. What's blocked, 2. Which agent is affected, 3. What decision/action is needed\"\n\nBut wait - I need to think about what I can actually DO about this:\n1. I can message Temujin to alert him about this task\n2. But if Temujin has no active session, will he receive it?\n\nLet me check if I can send a message to Temujin via the message tool.\n\nActually, looking at AGENTS.md more carefully:\n- \"Route to appropriate specialist agent\"\n- The routing is via `message({ to: \"<agent_id>\", text: \"...\" })`\n\nThe agent_id would be \"temujin\" based on the routing table.\n\nBut if Temujin doesn't have an active session, the message might not be delivered until his next heartbeat.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The HEARTBEAT.md says:\n- \"If something calls to me → do it (within NEVER rules)\"\n\nThis task DOES call to me - it's a high-priority task that's been pending for 2+ hours with an ASAP deadline. But:\n1. I cannot execute it myself (NEVER rule #1: \"NEVER execute specialist tasks yourself\")\n2. I should route it to Temujin\n\nBut Temujin isn't active right now. What can I do?\n\nOptions:\n1. Report this as needing attention (not HEARTBEAT_OK)\n2. Try to message Temujin anyway\n3. Check if there's a way to wake Temujin\n\nActually, looking at the AGENTS.md more carefully:\n- \"Step 2: Delegate via message()\"\n- \"message({ to: \"<agent_id>\", text: \"TASK: <what to do>\\nCONTEXT: <background>\\nURGENCY: high|normal|low\\nSUCCESS: <how to verify done>\" })\"\n\nI should try to message Temujin. Even if he's not active right now, the message might queue up for his next heartbeat.\n\nBut for the heartbeat response, should I say HEARTBEAT_OK or report the issue?\n\nLooking at HEARTBEAT.md again:\n- \"If Something Needs Attention: Report what's blocked, which agent is affected, what decision/action is needed\"\n\nI think this qualifies as something that needs attention - a HIGH priority task has been sitting for 2+ hours with no progress.\n\nLet me message Temujin about this task, then report it in my heartbeat response.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**Situation Assessment:**\n\n| Check | Status |\n|-------|--------|\n| Gateway | ✅ Running (RPC probe ok) |\n| Parse | ✅ 200 |\n| LLM Survivor | ✅ 200 |\n| Subagents | ✅ None stuck |\n| Critical Escalations | ✅ None |\n| Blocked Agents | ⚠️ **ISSUE DETECTED** |\n\n**Issue Found:**\n- **HIGH priority task pending 2+ hours**: \"Build Vision A of Parse for Agents\"\n- **Assigned to:** Temujin\n- **Status:** PENDING (no `.executing` file)\n- **Deadline:** ASAP - Danny waiting\n- **Problem:** Temujin has no active session right now\n\nI should route/alert Temujin about this stalled task:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_33c3a590f38941d5b73c9313","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","target":"temujin","message":"TASK: Build Vision A of Parse for Agents (HIGH PRIORITY - STALLED)\n\nCONTEXT: Your task at ~/tasks/high-1772694499.parse-for-agents-vision-a.md has been PENDING for 2+ hours. Deadline is ASAP - Danny is waiting for a testable frontend URL.\n\nURGENCY: HIGH\n\nCURRENT STATE:\n- Task created: 02:08 EST\n- Current time: 04:18 EST\n- Status: PENDING (no .executing marker found)\n- Spec files: ~/projects/parse-github/PARSE_FOR_AGENTS.md and SPEC-parse-for-agents.md\n\nACTION REQUIRED:\n1. If you're working on this, mark it as executing\n2. If blocked, report the blocker\n3. If not started, begin work or delegate back to Kublai\n\nSUCCESS: Working frontend at http://localhost:3000/agents with functional quality evaluator"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":22347,"output":1008,"cacheRead":3392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26747,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772702378381}}
{"type":"message","id":"943c085d","parentId":"832f5949","timestamp":"2026-03-05T09:20:32.968Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_33c3a590f38941d5b73c9313","toolName":"message","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"message\",\n  \"error\": \"Unknown target \\\"temujin\\\" for Signal. Hint: <E.164|uuid:ID|group:ID|signal:group:ID|signal:+E.164>\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"message","error":"Unknown target \"temujin\" for Signal. Hint: <E.164|uuid:ID|group:ID|signal:group:ID|signal:+E.164>"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772702432967}}
{"type":"message","id":"374c8306","parentId":"943c085d","timestamp":"2026-03-05T09:21:05.690Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah, the message tool tried to route via Signal, but \"temujin\" isn't a valid Signal target. I need to think about how to communicate with other agents.\n\nLooking at the tools and context:\n- The agents are configured in OpenClaw but they're not Signal contacts\n- I should use `sessions_send` to send a message to another session, not the `message` tool\n\nLet me try using sessions_send instead. The sessionKey would be something like \"agent:main:temujin\".\n\nActually, looking at the sessions_list output earlier, the only session found was \"agent:main:main\". This suggests the other agents (temujin, ogedei, etc.) don't have active sessions right now.\n\nHmm, this is a bit of a problem. How do I reach Temujin if he doesn't have an active session?\n\nLet me think about the architecture:\n1. Each agent has their own workspace directory\n2. They have heartbeat schedules\n3. They check their tasks directories\n\nSo maybe the best approach is to:\n1. Create a task file in Temujin's directory to flag this as urgent\n2. Wait for his next heartbeat\n\nBut wait - looking at HEARTBEAT.md more carefully:\n- \"Heartbeat: Every 30 minutes\"\n\nSo Temujin should check in every 30 minutes. But his session isn't active... \n\nActually, I realize I might be overthinking this. Let me check if there's a way to send a message to another agent's session. The sessions_send tool takes a sessionKey parameter.\n\nBut if the agent doesn't have an active session, the message might not be deliverable.\n\nLet me think about what I can control:\n1. I CAN create/modify task files in the agent directories\n2. I CAN use sessions_send if there's an active session\n3. I CAN report this as needing attention\n\nFor now, let me:\n1. Report this in my heartbeat response as something needing attention\n2. Note that Temujin needs to be alerted about the stalled task\n\nActually, looking at the HEARTBEAT.md again:\n- \"If Something Needs Attention\"\n- \"Report: 1. What's blocked 2. Which agent is affected 3. What decision/action is needed\"\n\nI should NOT reply HEARTBEAT_OK - I should report the issue. But I also tried to message Temujin and it failed.\n\nLet me check if there's a better way to alert an agent. Maybe I can create a flag file or update the task priority?","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The message tool can't reach Temujin directly via Signal - he's an agent, not a Signal contact. Let me try sessions_send to reach his session:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_56c545d402b1469b986c60bf","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:main:temujin","message":"ALERT: Your HIGH priority task \"Build Vision A of Parse for Agents\" has been PENDING for 2+ hours. Danny is waiting. Check your tasks directory and begin work or report blocker."}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":23416,"output":626,"cacheRead":3392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27434,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772702432968}}
