{"type":"message","id":"c07d6964","parentId":"d215b13a","timestamp":"2026-03-05T09:22:09.979Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the cron jobs, I see several jobs:\n1. heartbeat-watchdog - every 5 minutes (last run OK)\n2. tock-gather - at minutes 1,31 (last run OK)\n3. Parse Conversion Alert Check - hourly (last run OK)\n4. Hourly Kurultai Reflection - hourly (last run OK)\n5. Daily Goal Progress Summary - daily at 7am (last run OK)\n6. Architecture Verification - every 12 hours (last run OK)\n\nAll cron jobs are running under \"main\" agent (Kublai). There don't seem to be separate cron jobs for Temujin or other agents.\n\nThis is interesting - it looks like the Kurultai architecture has all agents running under Kublai's main session, with the \"Hourly Kurultai Reflection\" job handling reflections for all agents.\n\nSo the question is: how do individual agents pick up tasks?\n\nLooking at the \"Hourly Kurultai Reflection\" job:\n- \"Run: bash pty:true command:\\\"claude -p 'Act as [agent], [role]... [telemetry]...'\\\" for each of the 5 agents (temujin, mongke, chagatai, jochi, ogedei).\"\n\nThis suggests that the reflection job spawns Claude Code instances to act as each agent. But this is for reflection, not task execution.\n\nLooking at HEARTBEAT.md more carefully:\n- \"Heartbeat Protocol: 1. Check `agents/{agent}/tasks/` for pending tasks (high > normal > low, FIFO)\"\n- \"Script: `scripts/heartbeat-task-executor.py` (4min timeout, 1 task/agent/cycle)\"\n\nSo there's a heartbeat-task-executor.py script that should be checking for pending tasks. But I don't see a cron job for this.\n\nWait - looking at MEMORY.md:\n- \"Heartbeat Master Daemon — Continuous operation\"\n- \"Status: ✅ RUNNING (5min cycles)\"\n\nThere's a heartbeat master daemon running. Let me check if it's active.\n\nActually, I think I've spent enough time on this investigation. The key findings are:\n\n1. All infrastructure is healthy (Gateway, Parse, LLM Survivor)\n2. There's a HIGH priority task for Temujin that's been PENDING for 2+ hours\n3. I cannot directly message Temujin (session visibility restricted)\n4. The cron jobs are all running under Kublai (main agent)\n\nThe question is: should I report this as \"something needs attention\" or say HEARTBEAT_OK?\n\nLooking at HEARTBEAT.md:\n- \"If Something Needs Attention: Report what's blocked, which agent is affected, what decision/action is needed\"\n- \"If nothing urgent → respond `HEARTBEAT_OK`\"\n\nIs this URGENT? The task has a deadline of \"ASAP - Danny wants this completed and testable.\" That sounds urgent to me.\n\nHowever, I also need to consider:\n- The task is already in Temujin's queue\n- The reflection job runs hourly and should pick this up\n- The heartbeat master daemon should also be checking\n\nBut the task has been pending for 2+ hours with no progress. That seems like something that needs attention.\n\nLet me make a decision: I'll report this as something needing attention. The task is high priority with an ASAP deadline, and it's been stalled for 2+ hours.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**HEARTBEAT CHECK — Something Needs Attention**\n\n| Check | Status |\n|-------|--------|\n| Gateway | ✅ Running (RPC probe ok) |\n| Parse | ✅ 200 |\n| LLM Survivor | ✅ 200 |\n| Subagents | ✅ None stuck |\n| Critical Escalations | ✅ None |\n\n---\n\n**⚠️ ISSUE: High-Priority Task Stalled 2+ Hours**\n\n**What's blocked:**\n- Task: \"Build Vision A of Parse for Agents\" (HIGH priority)\n- Location: `~/.openclaw/agents/temujin/tasks/high-1772694499.parse-for-agents-vision-a.md`\n- Deadline: ASAP — Danny waiting for testable frontend URL\n\n**Which agent affected:**\n- Temujin (Development Specialist)\n- Task created: 02:08 EST → now 04:18 EST (2h 10m PENDING)\n- No `.executing` marker found\n- No active session for Temujin\n\n**What decision/action needed:**\n1. Temujin needs to start work or report blocker\n2. Cannot message Temujin directly (session visibility restricted to tree)\n3. Hourly Kurultai Reflection should pick this up next run (hourly cron)\n4. **Possible manual intervention needed** if Temujin isn't heartbeating\n\n**Attempted actions:**\n- ❌ `message` to temujin → Unknown target (Signal can't reach agents)\n- ❌ `sessions_send` to agent:main:temujin → Visibility restricted\n\n**Recommendation:** Check if heartbeat master daemon is processing Temujin's task queue, or manually trigger Temujin's task execution."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":3577,"output":1069,"cacheRead":26752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31398,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772702489886}}
