{"type":"message","id":"1119ac73","parentId":"b2a0a672","timestamp":"2026-03-05T09:33:40.675Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The tock.log shows interesting data:\n\n1. **tasks_done=0** for all entries - this means NO tasks have been completed by the tock system\n2. **queue** varies between 0 and 1 - there was a queue backlog at times\n3. **cron_err** shows some failures (Parse Conversion Alert Check had issues)\n4. **severity** varies between LOW, MEDIUM, and CRITICAL\n\nMost recent entry (04:31:18):\n- tasks_done=0, tasks_fail=0, queue=0, cron_err=0, severity=LOW\n\nThis tells me that the tock system is running, but **tasks_done=0 consistently**. This means either:\n1. No tasks are being processed\n2. The tasks aren't being tracked properly\n3. The task execution system isn't integrated with the tock logger\n\nThe fact that there's a \"file_pending queue backlog of 1 item\" at 03:01 and \"file_pending=1\" at 04:01 suggests there might be a pending task that's stuck.\n\nBut wait - the \"file_pending\" refers to a queue item, not necessarily the Temujin task. And the queue is now 0 (cleared).\n\nLet me check the watchdog.log to see what it shows:","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Interesting! The tock.log shows **tasks_done=0 consistently** - no tasks have been processed through the tock system. There was a \"file_pending queue backlog of 1 item\" at 03:01, but the queue is now 0.\n\nLet me check the watchdog.log for more context:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cf6969f08c1240e587953176","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -30 ~/.openclaw/agents/main/logs/watchdog.log 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":4322,"output":359,"cacheRead":31424,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36105,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772703190831}}
