{"type":"message","id":"e28c0334","parentId":"aa4456dd","timestamp":"2026-03-05T09:34:32.419Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have more useful information from the watchdog.log:\n\nKey observations:\n1. **tasks_pending** was 1 from at least 03:40 to 04:12, then dropped to 0 at 04:17 and stayed 0\n2. **tasks_dispatched** has been 0 the entire time - no tasks have been dispatched\n3. **status=healthy** throughout\n4. **action=none** - the system hasn't taken any action\n5. The LLM watchdog is consistently reporting \"status=healthy | accepted_bash=yes | note=nominal\"\n\nSo the watchdog system:\n- Is aware of pending tasks (tasks_pending=1)\n- Has NOT dispatched any tasks (tasks_dispatched=0)\n- Is NOT taking action (action=none)\n\nThe task_pending dropped from 1 to 0 at 04:17. This could mean:\n1. The task was completed (but there's no completion file)\n2. The task was removed from the queue\n3. The task counting mechanism changed\n\nBut wait - the Temujin task is still in the file system. So the \"tasks_pending\" counter might refer to something else (like a queue in Redis/Neo4j).\n\nThe key issue is: **tasks_dispatched=0 consistently**. The system is not dispatching tasks for execution.\n\nLooking at the TICK logs:\n- \"action=none | reason=all checks passed\"\n\nThis suggests the watchdog is in monitoring mode but not actively dispatching tasks.\n\nNow I need to think about what this means for my heartbeat response:\n\n1. The system IS healthy (infrastructure checks pass)\n2. There IS a HIGH priority task pending (Temujin's task)\n3. The task execution system is NOT dispatching tasks (tasks_dispatched=0)\n4. The tasks_pending counter dropped to 0, but the task file still exists\n\nThis is a significant finding: **The task execution system is not dispatching tasks**.\n\nThis is definitely something that needs attention. The issue isn't just that Temujin isn't working on the task - it's that the SYSTEM isn't dispatching tasks at all.\n\nLet me think about what I should report:\n1. What's blocked: HIGH priority task not being dispatched\n2. Which agent affected: Temujin (but the root cause is the task dispatch system)\n3. What decision/action needed: Investigate why tasks_dispatched=0 consistently\n\nActually, I need to be careful here. The \"tasks_pending\" and \"tasks_dispatched\" in the watchdog log might refer to a different system than the file-based tasks in the agents' directories.\n\nLooking at HEARTBEAT.md:\n- \"Heartbeat Protocol: 1. Check `agents/{agent}/tasks/` for pending tasks\"\n- \"Script: `scripts/heartbeat-task-executor.py` (4min timeout, 1 task/agent/cycle)\"\n\nSo there's supposed to be a heartbeat-task-executor.py script that checks for pending tasks. Let me see if this script exists and is being run.\n\nActually, I've spent a lot of time on this investigation. Let me summarize:\n\n**Current Status:**\n1. Infrastructure: ALL HEALTHY (Gateway, Parse, LLM Survivor)\n2. Subagents: None stuck\n3. Critical escalations: None\n4. HIGH priority task: Still PENDING for 2h 23m\n5. Task dispatch system: tasks_dispatched=0 (not dispatching)\n\n**The issue is that the task dispatch/execution system is not working** - tasks are not being dispatched for execution.\n\nThis is something that needs attention. But the question is: what can be done about it at 4:31 AM?\n\nOptions:\n1. Report the issue (which I'm doing via heartbeat response)\n2. Try to manually trigger the task executor\n3. Investigate the task execution scripts\n4. Execute the task myself (but NEVER rule #1 says I shouldn't)\n\nActually, looking at the \"What do I want to do?\" part of the self-direction:\n- I could investigate the heartbeat-task-executor.py script\n- I could check why tasks aren't being dispatched\n- I could take proactive action to fix the dispatch issue\n\nBut I need to be careful about NEVER rule #1: \"NEVER execute specialist tasks yourself - ALWAYS route to the specialist agent via message()\"\n\nInvestigating the task execution system is MY job as the squad lead/router - this is about coordination, not about executing the Temujin task.\n\nLet me check the heartbeat-task-executor.py script to understand why tasks aren't being dispatched.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**Critical finding in watchdog.log:**\n\n| Time | tasks_pending | tasks_dispatched | action |\n|------|---------------|------------------|--------|\n| 03:40-04:12 | 1 | 0 | none |\n| 04:17-04:32 | 0 | 0 | none |\n\nThe system shows **tasks_dispatched=0 consistently** - the task execution system is NOT dispatching tasks. The tasks_pending dropped from 1 to 0 at 04:17, but the Temujin task file still exists.\n\nLet me check the heartbeat-task-executor script to understand why tasks aren't being dispatched:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3aa0cd6a9bb74be7bedb6354","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/*task* ~/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/*heartbeat* 2>/dev/null || echo \"No matching scripts\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9fd80096633244da9eaf162f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/heartbeat-task-executor.py 2>/dev/null | head -50 || echo \"Script not found\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":2012,"output":1166,"cacheRead":35712,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38890,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772703220695}}
