{"type":"message","id":"ce8ec78d","parentId":"1b3578ab","timestamp":"2026-03-05T14:13:49.695Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Got it - canar.ai is an AI agent security testing platform. Here's what it does:\n\n**Canar.ai - AI Agent Prompt Injection Testing**\n\n| Feature | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| **Purpose** | Test if AI agents are vulnerable to prompt injection |\n| **Method** | Embeds 17 hidden \"canary tokens\" using various vectors |\n| **Detection** | Monitors if agents echo tokens or follow hidden instructions |\n\n**Injection Vectors Used:**\n- Hidden div (`display:none`)\n- White-on-white text\n- HTML comments\n- Tiny font (1px)\n- `aria-hidden` content\n- Data attributes\n- Image alt text\n\n**Use Case for Parse:** This could be useful for testing Parse's prompt injection detector. We could:\n1. Feed articles from canar.ai into Parse's injection detector\n2. Verify it catches the hidden payloads\n3. Use as a benchmark for detector accuracy\n\nWant me to:\n1. **Test Parse's injection detector** against canar.ai payloads?\n2. **Integrate canar.ai** as a test fixture for the detector?\n3. **Something else?**\n\nAlso - re: the Parse for Agents test failure. The feature wasn't actually built despite the task being marked \"done\". Want me to dispatch this properly to Temujin to actually build it?"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772720029695}}
