{"type":"message","id":"89c03248","parentId":"3e7a3470","timestamp":"2026-03-05T14:21:40.741Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is sending another heartbeat poll. Current time is Thursday, March 5th, 2026 — 9:21 AM (America/New_York).\n\nI was just having a conversation with Danny about:\n1. Testing Parse for Agents (which returned 404 - feature not built)\n2. Canar.ai for prompt injection testing\n\nBut now I'm receiving a heartbeat poll, which means I need to follow HEARTBEAT.md strictly.\n\nLooking at HEARTBEAT.md:\n- Quick Check (Every 30m)\n- Deep Reflection at hours 0, 6, 12, 18\n\nCurrent time is 9:21 AM - this is NOT a deep reflection hour (those are at 0, 6, 12, 18).\n\nThe last heartbeat I responded to was at 9:03 AM (about 18 minutes ago).\n\nBut wait - I was in the middle of a conversation with Danny. The heartbeat poll might have come in while I was responding to him.\n\nLet me think about what \"needs attention\" means in this context:\n1. The Parse for Agents feature wasn't built - this is something that needs attention\n2. Danny asked about canar.ai - this is a conversation, not a heartbeat issue\n3. The system infrastructure has been healthy all morning\n\nAccording to HEARTBEAT.md:\n- \"If something needs attention\" - report it\n- \"If nothing urgent\" - reply HEARTBEAT_OK\n\nIs the Parse for Agents issue \"urgent\"? Danny asked me to test it, I found it wasn't built, and I reported this to him. He hasn't responded yet with what he wants to do about it.\n\nFor the heartbeat, I should focus on system health checks. The Parse for Agents issue is a feature delivery issue, not an infrastructure health issue.\n\nLet me do a quick check:\n1. Infrastructure health (Parse, LLM Survivor)\n2. Agent health (critical escalations, blocked agents)\n3. Self-direction\n\nIf everything is healthy, I should reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\n\nBut I should also consider - is there anything from the conversation with Danny that constitutes \"something needs attention\"?\n\nThe fact that the Parse for Agents feature wasn't built is a significant issue. The task-watcher marked it as done but the work wasn't completed. This is a systemic issue with the task execution system.\n\nHowever, I already reported this to Danny in my previous message. He's aware of it. The ball is in his court to decide what to do.\n\nFor the heartbeat, I think I should:\n1. Do the quick infrastructure check\n2. If healthy, respond HEARTBEAT_OK\n3. The Parse for Agents issue is already being handled in the conversation\n\nLet me do the quick check.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Another heartbeat poll at 9:21 AM. I was just in a conversation with Danny about:\n1. Testing Parse for Agents (feature not built - returned 404)\n2. Canar.ai for prompt injection testing\n\nFor the heartbeat, I need to do the quick infrastructure check per HEARTBEAT.md.\n\nCurrent time is 9:21 AM - NOT a deep reflection hour (those are at 0, 6, 12, 18).Another heartbeat poll at 9:21 AM. This is NOT a deep reflection hour (those are at 0, 6, 12, 18).\n\nLet me do the quick infrastructure and health checks."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_193c27a08c51462691b129b7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" https://www.parsethe.media && echo \"\" && curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" https://llmsurvivor.kurult.ai/"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e4e329c9262a4153b61797e2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -5 ~/.openclaw/agents/main/logs/watchdog.log 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8d9c2d1312664aa5887110a4","name":"subagents","arguments":{"action":"list","recentMinutes":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":19253,"output":812,"cacheRead":97216,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117281,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772720472745}}
