{"type":"message","id":"9c291b52","parentId":"9c89f1e7","timestamp":"2026-03-05T14:53:22.845Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user (Danny) is asking me to have Temujin actually build the Parse for Agents feature using Claude Code. This is a direct instruction from the human operator.\n\nLooking at my role as Kublai (Squad Lead / Router), I need to:\n1. Route this task to Temujin (the Development Specialist)\n2. Use the proper routing mechanism\n\nAccording to AGENTS.md, I should route tasks to specialists via the `message()` tool. But earlier I found that I can't message Temujin directly via the message tool (he's not a Signal contact) and sessions_send is restricted to my session tree.\n\nHowever, I CAN create task files in Temujin's task directory. This is the file-based task routing mechanism.\n\nLet me create a new task file for Temujin to build the Parse for Agents feature using Claude Code.\n\nActually, looking at AGENTS.md more carefully:\n- \"Step 2: Delegate via message()\"\n- \"message({ to: \"<agent_id>\", text: \"TASK: <what to do>\\nCONTEXT: <background>\\nURGENCY: high|normal|low\\nSUCCESS: <how to verify done>\" })\"\n\nBut I already tried this and it failed because Temujin isn't a Signal contact.\n\nThe alternative is to create a task file in Temujin's task directory. This is how tasks get picked up by the task-watcher.\n\nLet me create a new task file for Temujin with clear instructions to use Claude Code to build the Parse for Agents feature.\n\nActually, looking at TOOLS.md:\n- \"Coding with Claude Code (via ACP)\"\n- \"sessions_spawn({ task: \"Your task here\", runtime: \"acp\", agentId: \"claude\", mode: \"run\" })\"\n\nWait - I could also use sessions_spawn with runtime=\"acp\" and agentId=\"claude\" to spawn a Claude Code session directly. But this would be ME doing the work, not Temujin.\n\nAccording to NEVER rule #1: \"NEVER execute specialist tasks yourself - ALWAYS route to the specialist agent via message()\"\n\nSo I should NOT use sessions_spawn directly to build this. I should route to Temujin.\n\nThe proper way is to create a task file in Temujin's task directory. The task-watcher will then pick it up and execute it.\n\nLet me create the task file now.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Danny wants me to have Temujin actually build the Parse for Agents feature using Claude Code. This is a direct instruction from the human operator.\n\nAs Kublai (Squad Lead / Router), I need to route this to Temujin (Development Specialist). Since I can't message Temujin directly via Signal, I'll create a task file in his task directory which the task-watcher will pick up.\n\nLet me create a new task for Temujin with clear instructions to use Claude Code to actually build the feature.Routing to Temujin now. Creating a task file for him to build the Parse for Agents feature using Claude Code."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_aa6f7ce0644749e4b402cc94","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/temujin/tasks/high-1772722500-parse-for-agents-build.md","content":"# TASK: Build Parse for Agents (Claude Code)\n\n**Priority:** HIGH\n**Created:** 2026-03-05 09:55 EST\n**Assigned by:** Kublai (per Danny's direct instruction)\n**Status:** PENDING\n\n---\n\n## Objective\n\n**ACTUALLY BUILD** the Parse for Agents feature using Claude Code. The previous task was marked \"done\" but the feature was never built or deployed. Danny needs a working frontend URL to test.\n\n---\n\n## Critical Context\n\n**DO NOT just mark this task as done without building the feature.**\n\nThe previous task (high-1772694499) was marked \"success\" by the task-watcher but the feature doesn't exist:\n- `/agents` returns 404\n- `/api/v1/agents-test/models` returns 404\n- `/api/v1/agents-test/evaluators` returns 404\n\n**You must actually build and deploy this feature.**\n\n---\n\n## How to Work\n\nUse Claude Code to build this. Run commands like:\n\n```bash\ncd ~/projects/parse-github\nclaude --dangerously-skip-permissions \"Build the Parse for Agents feature per PARSE_FOR_AGENTS.md spec. Create /agents frontend page and /api/v1/agents-test/* API endpoints. Deploy to Railway when complete.\"\n```\n\nOr use pty mode for interactive work:\n```bash\nbash pty:true workdir:~/projects/parse-github command:\"claude -p 'Build Parse for Agents per PARSE_FOR_AGENTS.md'\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Spec Files\n\n- `~/projects/parse-github/PARSE_FOR_AGENTS.md`\n- `~/projects/parse-github/SPEC-parse-for-agents.md`\n\n---\n\n## Deliverables\n\n### 1. Frontend at `/agents`\n- Prompt template editor with `{{input}}` interpolation\n- Model selector (multiple providers)\n- Evaluator checkboxes (quality, cost, latency)\n- Temperature/max tokens configuration\n- Real-time polling for results\n- Results display with quality scores, cost metrics, latency\n\n### 2. API Endpoints\n- `POST /api/v1/evaluate` - Submit prompt evaluation (returns 202 with job ID)\n- `GET /api/v1/evaluate/[id]` - Poll for results\n- `GET /api/v1/agents-test/models` - List supported models\n- `GET /api/v1/agents-test/evaluators` - List available evaluators\n\n### 3. Evaluators (Must Actually Work)\n- **Cost** - Token counting, pricing per model\n- **Latency** - Timing, tokens per second\n- **Quality** - LLM-as-judge using OpenAI (gpt-4o-mini) or DeepSeek\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n**Danny needs to be able to test this at https://www.parsethe.media/agents**\n\n1. `curl https://www.parsethe.media/agents` returns 200 (not 404)\n2. `curl https://www.parsethe.media/api/v1/agents-test/models` returns JSON\n3. Can submit a prompt via the frontend and see results\n4. Quality evaluator returns actual LLM judgment (not mock)\n\n---\n\n## Deadline\n\n**IMMEDIATE** - Danny is waiting to test.\n\n---\n\n## Report Back\n\nWhen complete, report to Kublai with:\n1. Frontend URL confirmation (should be https://www.parsethe.media/agents)\n2. Screenshot or curl output showing it works\n3. Any issues encountered\n\n---\n\n**Assigned by:** Kublai (Squad Lead)\n**Project:** Parse for Agents\n**Method:** Claude Code (ACP runtime)\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":114813,"output":1429,"cacheRead":3392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":119634,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772722357849}}
