{"type":"message","id":"51bfa1a6","parentId":"abfc5202","timestamp":"2026-03-05T14:53:46.282Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I've created the task file for Temujin. Now I should let Danny know that I've routed this to Temujin and that the task-watcher should pick it up within 10 seconds (since it polls every 10 seconds).\n\nI should also mention that I've made it clear in the task that:\n1. This must be ACTUALLY built, not just marked as done\n2. Claude Code should be used\n3. Danny is waiting to test it\n4. The deliverables include actual working endpoints\n\nLet me respond to Danny.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Task routed to Temujin. The task file has been created at:\n```\n~/.openclaw/agents/temujin/tasks/high-1772722500-parse-for-agents-build.md\n```\n\n**Task Details:**\n- **Priority:** HIGH\n- **Method:** Claude Code (as you requested)\n- **Deadline:** IMMEDIATE\n- **Deliverable:** Working frontend at https://www.parsethe.media/agents\n\n**Key Instructions I Included:**\n1. **DO NOT just mark this task as done without building** - explicit warning about the previous failure\n2. Use Claude Code with `claude --dangerously-skip-permissions` \n3. Build the `/agents` frontend AND `/api/v1/agents-test/*` API endpoints\n4. Deploy to Railway\n5. Report back with working URL confirmation\n\nThe task-watcher daemon polls every 10 seconds, so Temujin should pick this up immediately.\n\nI'll monitor for completion and let you know when the feature is ready to test."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":116282,"output":331,"cacheRead":3392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":120005,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772722402883}}
