{"type":"message","id":"a13b0870","parentId":"46815b1c","timestamp":"2026-03-05T15:07:25.575Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have all 5 agent reflections. Let me compile the final summary report:\n\n---\n\n# Kurultai Hourly Reflection — 10:02 AM EST, March 5, 2026\n\n**Period:** 9:04 AM → 10:02 AM EST (1 hour)\n**Previous Reflection:** 9:04 AM EST, March 5, 2026\n\n---\n\n## Executive Summary\n\n**System Status:** Gateway HEALTHY, Neo4j UP, Redis UP, 2/2 cron jobs configured\n**Total Tasks Completed:** 0 (all agents idle 15+ consecutive hours)\n**Agents Active:** 0/5\n**Agents Idle:** 5/5 (Temujin, Mongke, Chagatai, Jochi, Ogedei all report zero output)\n**Queue Depth:** 0 tasks in agent queues (but kublai has meta-tasks from tock)\n\n**Critical Pattern:** Full system idle for 15+ hours. Auto-dispatch mechanism non-functional. Tock generates investigation tasks about its own investigation tasks (second-order circular pattern).\n\n---\n\n## Agent Reflections\n\n### Temujin (Developer)\n**Grade: F** | **Status: IDLE** | **Tasks: 0**\n\n- **Worst Moment:** Parse MVP assigned 9+ hours with zero progress. Rules T3/T4 specify self-assign but no trigger.\n- **New Rule:** WHEN invoked via reflection AND Parse MVP IN_PROGRESS with no code THEN begin local implementation directly INSTEAD OF waiting for dispatch.\n- **Feedback (HIGH):** Spawn-consumer.sh \"syntax error line 312\" is phantom (file is 37 lines). Clean up stale telemetry.\n- **Proposed:** Build /v1/evaluate endpoint (HIGH), Fix reflection cron error (NORMAL)\n\n### Mongke (Researcher)\n**Grade: F** | **Status: IDLE** | **Tasks: 0**\n\n- **Worst Moment:** Rule M1 (auto-generate research when idle 2+ hours) never fired in 15 hours.\n- **New Rule:** WHEN reflection runs AND 0 pending tasks THEN produce deliverable inline INSTEAD OF just proposing.\n- **Feedback (HIGH):** Parse competitive research overdue for $1500 MRR goal. Need standing daily research cron at 08:00.\n- **Proposed:** Parse SaaS competitive landscape (HIGH), API pricing research (HIGH)\n\n### Chagatai (Writer)\n**Grade: D** | **Status: IDLE** | **Tasks: 0**\n\n- **Worst Moment:** Architecture doc already exists at docs/architecture.md (813 lines) — was never told. Two proposed tasks from 9:04 undispatched.\n- **New Rule:** WHEN reflection fires AND content needs identified THEN produce deliverable inline INSTEAD OF listing proposals.\n- **DELIVERABLE PRODUCED:** Parse for Agents Product Brief (draft) — includes API spec, evaluators, tech stack, success criteria.\n- **Feedback (HIGH):** Remove architecture doc from content needs. Parse Product Brief is real gap.\n- **Proposed:** Save Product Brief (HIGH), Kurultai README (NORMAL)\n\n### Jochi (Analyst)\n**Grade: D** | **Status: IDLE** | **Tasks: 0**\n\n- **Worst Moment:** Triage task landed at 10:03 but no session to pick it up. Second-order circular pattern: tock creates task for kublai → kublai gets stalled → tock creates triage task about kublai's stall.\n- **New Rule:** WHEN kublai-actions creates \"Triage stalled agent\" AND stalled agent's only task is auto-generated THEN skip alert INSTEAD OF creating meta-tasks.\n- **Feedback (HIGH):** session-runner.sh committed but not running as cron/daemon. All agents show model:none, sessions:0.\n- **Proposed:** Wire session-runner to cron (HIGH), Add self-referential stall guard (NORMAL)\n\n### Ogedei (Ops)\n**Grade: D** | **Status: IDLE** | **Tasks: 0**\n\n- **Worst Moment:** Hourly Kurultai Reflection cron has consecutive_errors=1 (586s runtime). System investigating why no work exists.\n- **New Rule:** WHEN all agents at 0 tasks AND idle > 1hr THEN self-assign investigation INSTEAD OF waiting.\n- **Feedback (HIGH):** System in dead loop — only active work is investigating why there's no active work. Bootstrap real work manually.\n- **Proposed:** Fix reflection cron error (HIGH), Audit circular routing (HIGH)\n\n---\n\n## Cross-Agent Patterns\n\n### Critical Issues\n1. **Auto-Dispatch Not Functional:** session-runner.sh exists but not wired to cron. All agents show model:none, sessions:0.\n2. **Circular Meta-Task Generation:** Tock creates CRITICAL tasks → kublai gets them → tock sees kublai stalled → creates triage task. Self-referential loop.\n3. **Rules Without Triggers:** All 5 agents have behavioral rules but nothing invokes them.\n4. **Stale Telemetry:** \"spawn-consumer line 312\" finding is phantom (file is 37 lines).\n5. **Reflection Cron Degraded:** consecutive_errors=1, 586s runtime.\n\n### Root Cause Analysis\n| Symptom | Root Cause | Fix |\n|---------|------------|-----|\n| All agents idle | No session-runner cron | Wire session-runner.sh to crontab |\n| Circular meta-tasks | Tock→actions feedback loop | Skip stalled alerts for auto-generated tasks |\n| Rules not enforced | No trigger mechanism | Add heartbeat→rule check hook |\n| Reflection errors | Long runtime (586s) | Optimize or timeout |\n\n---\n\n## System Health\n\n| Metric | Status |\n|--------|--------|\n| Gateway | HEALTHY |\n| Redis | UP (PONG) |\n| Neo4j | UP (v2026.01.4) |\n| Cron Jobs | 2/2 configured |\n| heartbeat-watchdog.err | 0 bytes (clean) |\n| Tasks Pending | 0 in agent queues |\n| Tasks Dispatched | 0 |\n| Tock Severity | MEDIUM |\n\n---\n\n## Actions Required (Next Hour)\n\n### Immediate\n1. **(HIGH) Wire session-runner.sh to cron** → Ogedei/Temujin\n   - Add to crontab, run every 2-5 minutes\n   - Enables auto-dispatch to idle agents\n\n2. **(HIGH) Add self-referential stall guard** → Temujin\n   - Modify kublai-actions.py to skip stalled alerts for auto-generated tasks\n\n3. **(NORMAL) Save Chagatai's Product Brief** → Kublai\n   - Chagatai produced inline deliverable — save to docs/parse-for-agents-brief.md\n\n4. **(NORMAL) Clean up stale telemetry** → Ogedei\n   - Remove phantom \"line 312\" finding\n\n### Architectural\n1. Create standing daily research cron for Mongke (08:00 EST)\n2. Fix reflection cron consecutive_errors (investigate 586s runtime)\n3. Bootstrap Parse for Agents MVP manually to Temujin\n\n---\n\n## Active Rules Status\n\n| Agent | Rule | Status |\n|-------|------|--------|\n| Temujin | T3/T4: anti-idle self-assign | FAILED (no trigger) |\n| Mongke | M1: auto-generate research | FAILED (no trigger) |\n| Chagatai | C2: produce inline deliverable | **FOLLOWED** (Product Brief draft) |\n| Jochi | J1: proactive telemetry | FAILED (no session) |\n| Ogedei | O1: audit when idle | FAILED (no trigger) |\n\n---\n\n## The Momentum Question\n\n**What should happen next?**\n\n1. **Wire session-runner.sh to cron** — This is the #1 blocker. Without it, all 5 agents remain decorative.\n2. **Save Chagatai's Product Brief** — Concrete deliverable produced, should be persisted.\n3. **Break circular meta-task loop** — Suppress self-referential stalled-agent alerts.\n4. **Bootstrap Parse MVP** — Manual dispatch to Temujin since auto-dispatch broken.\n\n---\n\n## Final Assessment\n\n**Grade: D-** (marginal improvement)\n\nZero productivity for 15+ consecutive hours. However:\n- Chagatai produced inline deliverable (Product Brief draft)\n- Circular triage fix already in place at line 351\n- System health maintained (all services UP)\n- Root causes clearly identified\n\n**The Kurultai remains in coordination failure, but the fixes are known and documented.** Primary action: wire session-runner.sh to cron to enable auto-dispatch.\n\n---\n\n*Reflection complete at 10:02 AM EST, March 5, 2026*\n*Generated by Kublai using Claude Code for all 5 agent reflections*"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772723245575}}
{"type":"message","id":"58250a0e","parentId":"46815b1c","timestamp":"2026-03-05T15:07:52.958Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see clearly:\n\n**My task (`high-1772722500-parse-for-agents-build.md`):**\n- Executed: 2026-03-05T09:53:34.229166\n- Success: True\n\nSo the task WAS executed and marked as success=True. But the feature still doesn't exist (I tested it earlier and got 404).\n\nThis is the same problem as before - the task-watcher is marking tasks as \"success\" but the actual work isn't being done.\n\nLooking at the other tasks that were executed:\n- `temujin/high-1772721000-circular-triage-fix.md` - 09:12:57\n- `temujin/high-1772721001-auto-dispatch-cron.md` - 09:13:10\n- `temujin/high-1772578840.md` - 09:19:24\n- `temujin/high-1772722500-parse-for-agents-build.md` - 09:53:34\n\nSo Temujin's tasks ARE being executed, but they're being marked as \"success\" without actually completing the work.\n\nThe problem is that the task-watcher is calling `openclaw agent --agent temujin --message <task>` and the agent is responding (which counts as \"success\"), but the agent isn't actually doing the coding work.\n\nThis is a fundamental issue with the task execution system - it's not actually using Claude Code to build things. It's just having the agent \"acknowledge\" the task and marking it as done.\n\nFor the user's question \"is temujin still working\" - the answer is:\n1. The task was picked up and \"executed\" at 09:53:34\n2. It was marked as \"success\"\n3. But the feature still doesn't exist (404 on /agents)\n4. The task execution system is broken - it's not actually building things\n\nI should report this clearly.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Found it. Here's the status:\n\n**Task Execution Status:**\n\n| Task | Executed | Success |\n|------|----------|---------|\n| `temujin/high-1772722500-parse-for-agents-build.md` | 09:53:34 | True |\n\n**The problem:** The task was marked as \"success\" but the feature STILL doesn't exist. Let me verify:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_dc2a4ae6bb724d85a0bb99dc","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" https://www.parsethe.media/agents"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_afbde566d7fa446393d538a5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s https://www.parsethe.media/api/v1/agents-test/models 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":107932,"output":571,"cacheRead":8768,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117271,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772723242088}}
