{"type":"message","id":"7c9c16f5","parentId":"d731c11f","timestamp":"2026-03-05T15:08:24.123Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The test confirms that the feature still doesn't exist - both /agents and /api/v1/agents-test/models return 404.\n\nSo the answer to \"is temujin still working\" is:\n\n1. The task WAS executed at 09:53:34 and marked as \"success\"\n2. But the feature STILL doesn't exist (404 on all endpoints)\n3. The task execution system is fundamentally broken - it's marking tasks as successful without actually doing the work\n\nThis is a critical issue with the task execution system. The task-watcher is calling the agent, the agent responds (which counts as \"success\"), but the agent isn't actually using Claude Code to build things.\n\nThe problem is:\n1. Task-watcher spawns an agent session\n2. Agent reads the task and responds\n3. Response counts as \"success\"\n4. But no actual coding/building happens\n\nThis is a systemic failure in the task execution architecture.\n\nFor the user's question - I should report:\n1. The task was executed and marked as success\n2. But the feature still doesn't exist\n3. The task execution system isn't actually building things - it's just acknowledging tasks","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**Temujin Status - PROBLEM IDENTIFIED**\n\n| Check | Result |\n|-------|--------|\n| Task executed? | Yes - 09:53:34 |\n| Marked success? | Yes - True |\n| Feature built? | **NO** - Still 404 |\n\n**The task execution system is broken.** Tasks are being marked as \"success\" without any actual work being done.\n\n**What's happening:**\n1. Task-watcher picks up the task\n2. Spawns an agent session with `openclaw agent --agent temujin`\n3. Agent acknowledges the task\n4. System marks it as \"success\"\n5. **But no actual Claude Code execution happens** - no code is written, no deployment occurs\n\n**Root cause:** The task execution system doesn't actually invoke Claude Code to build things. It just has the agent \"read and acknowledge\" the task, which counts as success.\n\n**The feature at `/agents` still returns 404** despite multiple tasks being marked as \"success.\"\n\n**What needs to happen:** Someone (Danny or a human) needs to actually run Claude Code directly to build this feature. The automated task execution system cannot currently execute coding work - it only acknowledges tasks."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":7728,"output":498,"cacheRead":116672,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":124898,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772723273613}}
