{"type":"message","id":"30187528","parentId":"9cba0d2d","timestamp":"2026-03-05T16:14:31.765Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The quick check results show:\n\n1. Infrastructure:\n   - Parse: 200 ✅\n   - LLM Survivor: 200 ✅\n\n2. Watchdog log (most recent at 11:12:24):\n   - status=healthy ✅\n   - tasks_pending=1 (up from 0 - there's a new pending task!)\n   - errors=8 (down from 10)\n   - neo4j=up, redis=up ✅\n   - action=none, reason=all checks passed ✅\n\nInteresting - tasks_pending=1 now. There's a new pending task somewhere. This could be:\n1. A task I created\n2. A task created by another agent\n3. Something else\n\nBut the system is healthy overall. The tasks_pending=1 just means there's a task waiting to be executed. This is normal operation.\n\nFor the heartbeat:\n- Infrastructure is healthy\n- tasks_pending=1 (there's a task waiting)\n- No urgent infrastructure issues\n\nShould I report this as \"something needs attention\"? Looking at HEARTBEAT.md:\n- \"If something calls to me → do it (within NEVER rules)\"\n- \"If nothing urgent → respond `HEARTBEAT_OK`\"\n\nIs a single pending task \"urgent\"? Not really - this is normal operation. The task-watcher should pick it up.\n\nI should respond with HEARTBEAT_OK.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The quick check results show:\n\n1. Infrastructure:\n   - Parse: 200 ✅\n   - LLM Survivor: 200 ✅\n\n2. Watchdog log (most recent at 11:12:24):\n   - status=healthy ✅\n   - tasks_pending=1 (up from 0 - there's a new pending task)\n   - errors=8 (down from 10)\n   - neo4j=up, redis=up ✅\n   - action=none, reason=all checks passed ✅\n\nInteresting - tasks_pending=1 now. There's a pending task waiting to be executed. But the system is healthy overall - this is normal operation.\n\nFor the heartbeat:\n- Infrastructure is healthy\n- tasks_pending=1 (normal - task waiting to be picked up)\n- No urgent infrastructure issues\n\nI should respond with HEARTBEAT_OK.Quick check