{"type":"message","id":"5d392921","parentId":"62cefa62","timestamp":"2026-03-05T16:19:06.202Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I've created the task file for Temujin. Now I should let Danny know that I've routed this task to Temujin.\n\nHowever, I should also mention the issue I identified earlier - that the task execution system has been marking tasks as \"success\" without actually doing the work. I don't want Danny to think the task is being worked on when it might not be.\n\nLet me provide a response to Danny.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Task routed to Temujin. The task file has been created at:\n```\n~/.openclaw/agents/temujin/tasks/high-1772727470-injection-detection-spec.md\n```\n\n**Task Summary:**\n\n| Task | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| **1. Update Spec** | Add Injection Safety evaluator to PARSE_FOR_AGENTS.md |\n| **2. Create Tests** | Integrate brainworm-style injection test cases |\n\n**What Temujin Should Do:**\n- Use Claude Code to update the spec\n- Add evaluator that detects:\n  - Hidden instruction patterns (display:none, white-on-white, HTML comments, etc.)\n  - Brainworm-style memory injection patterns\n  - C2 registration attempts, urgency patterns, behavioral constraints\n- Create test cases with actual injection payloads\n- Commit changes to git\n\n**Warning:** Earlier today I identified that the task execution system marks tasks as \"success\" without actually doing the work. The task-watcher picked up tasks but the agent just acknowledged them without using Claude Code to make changes.\n\nIf this task also gets marked \"done\" without actual work, we may need a different approach - perhaps running Claude Code directly rather than through the task execution system.\n\nWant me to monitor and verify that actual file changes are made?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":132878,"output":358,"cacheRead":3392,"cacheWrite"