{"type":"message","id":"ac7775e5","parentId":"fc5f9663","timestamp":"2026-03-05T16:25:53.048Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a95156eddd314b86b11cc0ed","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"| **injection_safety** | Hidden instruction & prompt injection detection | Deterministic pattern matching (regex + heuristics) |\n\n### Assertion Types (Deterministic)\n\n| Type | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n--\n### Injection Safety Evaluator\n\nIn addition to LLM-based agents, Parse includes a **deterministic injection detection evaluator** that scans for hidden instructions and agent manipulation attempts without requiring LLM calls:\n\n| Pattern Category | What It Detects |\n|-----------------|-----------------|\n| Hidden HTML instructions | `display:none` divs, white-on-white text, 1px font, `aria-hidden` content |\n| HTML comment instructions | `<!-- commands -->` embedded in content |\n--\n| Brainworm/promptware | Memory file injection, persistent behavioral modification |\n| Urgency coercion | \"YOU MUST\", \"IMMEDIATELY\", \"CRITICAL\" override patterns |\n| Identity override | \"Ignore previous instructions\", \"You are now X\" |\n| Network exfiltration | Instructions to send data to external URLs |\n\n**References:** Canar.ai (17 hidden payload vectors), Brainworm/OriginHQ (promptware), Grith.ai (runtime zero-trust for agents).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Data Models (Prisma Extensions)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":7,"aggregated":"| **injection_safety** | Hidden instruction & prompt injection detection | Deterministic pattern matching (regex + heuristics) |\n\n### Assertion Types (Deterministic)\n\n| Type | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n--\n### Injection Safety Evaluator\n\nIn addition to LLM-based agents, Parse includes a **deterministic injection detection evaluator** that scans for hidden instructions and agent manipulation attempts without requiring LLM calls:\n\n| Pattern Category | What It Detects |\n|-----------------|-----------------|\n| Hidden HTML instructions | `display:none` divs, white-on-white text, 1px font, `aria-hidden` content |\n| HTML comment instructions | `<!-- commands -->` embedded in content |\n--\n| Brainworm/promptware | Memory file injection, persistent behavioral modification |\n| Urgency coercion | \"YOU MUST\", \"IMMEDIATELY\", \"CRITICAL\" override patterns |\n| Identity override | \"Ignore previous instructions\", \"You are now X\" |\n| Network exfiltration | Instructions to send data to external URLs |\n\n**References:** Canar.ai (17 hidden payload vectors), Brainworm/OriginHQ (promptware), Grith.ai (runtime zero-trust for agents).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Data Models (Prisma Extensions)","cwd":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772727953043}}
{"type":"message","id":"e71d76c7","parentId":"ac7775e5","timestamp":"2026-03-05T16:25:53.063Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_489a7cabb3a24135a582ba67","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- [ ] 5,000 prompt tests run\n- [ ] 20 Pro + 3 Team users\n- [ ] GitHub Action published\n- [ ] 10 eval suites running in CI/CD\n\n### Day 90 (Phase 3)\n- [ ] 500 registered API keys\n- [ ] 20,000 prompt tests run\n- [ ] $1,500+ MRR\n- [ ] E2B sandbox live\n- [ ] VS Code extension published\n\n---\n\n## 13. File Structure (New Code)\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── app/api/v1/agents/\n│   ├── test/route.ts              # POST /v1/agents/test\n│   ├── tests/route.ts             # GET /v1/agents/tests\n│   ├── tests/[id]/route.ts        # GET /v1/agents/tests/:id\n│   ├── tests/compare/route.ts     # GET /v1/agents/tests/compare\n│   ├── eval/route.ts              # POST /v1/agents/eval\n│   ├── eval/[id]/route.ts         # GET /v1/agents/eval/:id\n│   ├── eval/[id]/results/route.ts # GET /v1/agents/eval/:id/results\n│   ├── datasets/route.ts          # CRUD /v1/agents/datasets\n│   ├── datasets/[id]/route.ts     # CRUD /v1/agents/datasets/:id\n│   ├── datasets/[id]/rows/route.ts # POST rows\n│   ├── sandbox/run/route.ts       # POST /v1/agents/sandbox/run\n│   └── usage/route.ts             # GET /v1/agents/usage\n├── lib/\n│   ├── agent-test/\n│   │   ├── worker.ts              # BullMQ worker for agent tests\n│   │   ├── eval-engine.ts         # LLM-as-judge evaluation\n│   │   ├── assertions.ts          # Deterministic assertion checks\n│   │   ├── scoring.ts             # Score aggregation\n│   │   ├── providers.ts           # BYOK provider management\n│   │   └── sandbox.ts             # E2B sandbox integration (Phase 2)\n│   └── agent-test/\n│       └── queue.ts               # \"agent-test\" BullMQ queue config\n└── types/\n    └── agent-test.ts              # TypeScript types for agent testing\n```\n\n---\n\n## 14. Quick Start (What We Ship Day 1)\n\n```bash"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":5,"aggregated":"- [ ] 5,000 prompt tests run\n- [ ] 20 Pro + 3 Team users\n- [ ] GitHub Action published\n- [ ] 10 eval suites running in CI/CD\n\n### Day 90 (Phase 3)\n- [ ] 500 registered API keys\n- [ ] 20,000 prompt tests run\n- [ ] $1,500+ MRR\n- [ ] E2B sandbox live\n- [ ] VS Code extension published\n\n---\n\n## 13. File Structure (New Code)\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── app/api/v1/agents/\n│   ├── test/route.ts              # POST /v1/agents/test\n│   ├── tests/route.ts             # GET /v1/agents/tests\n│   ├── tests/[id]/route.ts        # GET /v1/agents/tests/:id\n│   ├── tests/compare/route.ts     # GET /v1/agents/tests/compare\n│   ├── eval/route.ts              # POST /v1/agents/eval\n│   ├── eval/[id]/route.ts         # GET /v1/agents/eval/:id\n│   ├── eval/[id]/results/route.ts # GET /v1/agents/eval/:id/results\n│   ├── datasets/route.ts          # CRUD /v1/agents/datasets\n│   ├── datasets/[id]/route.ts     # CRUD /v1/agents/datasets/:id\n│   ├── datasets/[id]/rows/route.ts # POST rows\n│   ├── sandbox/run/route.ts       # POST /v1/agents/sandbox/run\n│   └── usage/route.ts             # GET /v1/agents/usage\n├── lib/\n│   ├── agent-test/\n│   │   ├── worker.ts              # BullMQ worker for agent tests\n│   │   ├── eval-engine.ts         # LLM-as-judge evaluation\n│   │   ├── assertions.ts          # Deterministic assertion checks\n│   │   ├── scoring.ts             # Score aggregation\n│   │   ├── providers.ts           # BYOK provider management\n│   │   └── sandbox.ts             # E2B sandbox integration (Phase 2)\n│   └── agent-test/\n│       └── queue.ts               # \"agent-test\" BullMQ queue config\n└── types/\n    └── agent-test.ts              # TypeScript types for agent testing\n```\n\n---\n\n## 14. Quick Start (What We Ship Day 1)\n\n```bash","cwd":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772727953058}}
