{"type":"message","id":"ab8f18e5","parentId":"7ac6720a","timestamp":"2026-03-05T16:49:01.629Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user has provided me with Google Workspace credentials for Kublai and wants me to set up Google Workspace using CLI. I've already saved the credentials to a secure file.\n\nNow I've confirmed that `gws` is installed (version 0.3.5). I need to set up authentication.\n\nThe gws-shared skill mentions two authentication methods:\n1. Browser-based OAuth (interactive): `gws auth login`\n2. Service Account: `export GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/path/to/key.json`\n\nSince the user gave me email/password credentials (not a service account key), I need to use browser-based OAuth. However, this requires interactive browser access to complete the OAuth flow.\n\nLet me try to initiate the `gws auth login` process. This will likely open a browser for authentication.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"`gws` is installed (version 0.3.5). Now I need to set up authentication. Since the user provided email/password credentials, I'll use browser-based OAuth. Let me initiate the authentication flow:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e529559dbf794643bdbdd94d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gws auth login --help 2>/dev/null || gws auth --help 2>/dev/null || gws --help 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":295,"output":253,"cacheRead":136768,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":137316,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772729319847}}
{"type":"message","id":"c9ec1cb7","parentId":"ab8f18e5","timestamp":"2026-03-05T16:49:01.840Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_e529559dbf794643bdbdd94d","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": 401,\n    \"message\": \"No OAuth client configured.\\n\\nEither:\\n  1. Run `gws auth setup` to configure a GCP project and OAuth client\\n  2. Download client_secret.json from Google Cloud Console and save it to:\\n     ~/.config/gws/client_secret.json\\n  3. Set env vars: GOOGLE_WORKSPACE_CLI_CLIENT_ID and GOOGLE_WORKSPACE_CLI_CLIENT_SECRET\",\n    \"reason\": \"authError\"\n  }\n}\nUsage: gws auth <login|setup|status|export|logout>\n\n  login   Authenticate via OAuth2 (opens browser)\n          --readonly   Request read-only scopes\n          --full       Request all scopes incl. pubsub + cloud-platform\n                       (may trigger restricted_client for unverified apps)\n          --scopes     Comma-separated custom scopes\n  setup   Configure GCP project + OAuth client (requires gcloud)\n          --project    Use a specific GCP project\n  status  Show current authentication state\n  export  Print decrypted credentials to stdout\n  logout  Clear saved credentials and token cache"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":191,"aggregated":"{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": 401,\n    \"message\": \"No OAuth client configured.\\n\\nEither:\\n  1. Run `gws auth setup` to configure a GCP project and OAuth client\\n  2. Download client_secret.json from Google Cloud Console and save it to:\\n     ~/.config/gws/client_secret.json\\n  3. Set env vars: GOOGLE_WORKSPACE_CLI_CLIENT_ID and GOOGLE_WORKSPACE_CLI_CLIENT_SECRET\",\n    \"reason\": \"authError\"\n  }\n}\nUsage: gws auth <login|setup|status|export|logout>\n\n  login   Authenticate via OAuth2 (opens browser)\n          --readonly   Request read-only scopes\n          --full       Request all scopes incl. pubsub + cloud-platform\n                       (may trigger restricted_client for unverified apps)\n          --scopes     Comma-separated custom scopes\n  setup   Configure GCP project + OAuth client (requires gcloud)\n          --project    Use a specific GCP project\n  status  Show current authentication state\n  export  Print decrypted credentials to stdout\n  logout  Clear saved credentials and token cache","cwd":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772729341836}}
{"type":"message","id":"7a80b704","parentId":"c9ec1cb7","timestamp":"2026-03-05T16:49:39.486Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user has provided me with Google Workspace credentials for Kublai and wants me to set up Google Workspace using CLI. I've already saved the credentials to a secure file.\n\nThe `gws auth login` command requires an OAuth client to be configured first. The error message shows three options:\n\n1. Run `gws auth setup` to configure a GCP project and OAuth client\n2. Download client_secret.json from Google Cloud Console and save it to ~/.config/gws/client_secret.json\n3. Set env vars: GOOGLE_WORKSPACE_CLI_CLIENT_ID and GOOGLE_WORKSPACE_CLI_CLIENT_SECRET\n\nSince I don't have a client_secret.json or the env vars set up, I need to either:\n1. Run `gws auth setup` (requires gcloud)\n2. Ask the user to provide client_secret.json\n\nLet me try `gws auth setup` to see if it can automatically configure things.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The user has provided me with Google Workspace credentials for Kublai and wants me to set up Google Workspace using CLI. I've already saved the credentials to a secure file.\n\nNow I see that `gws auth login` requires an OAuth client to be configured first. The error message shows three options:\n\n1. Run `gws auth setup` to configure a GCP project and OAuth client\n2. Download client_secret.json from Google Cloud Console and save it to ~/.config/gws/client_secret.json\n3. Set env vars: GOOGLE_WORKSPACE_CLI_CLIENT_ID and GOOGLE_WORKSPACE_CLI_CLIENT_SECRET\n\nLet me try `gws auth setup` to configure the OAuth client:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_df572333343b45708d3f8313","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gws auth setup --help 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":135696,"output":340,"cacheRead":1856,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":137892,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":