{"type":"message","id":"7c878801","parentId":"8a809b9e","timestamp":"2026-03-05T16:55:19.908Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user has provided me with Google Workspace credentials for Kublai and wants me to set up Google Workspace using CLI. I've already saved the credentials to a secure file.\n\nThe `gws auth setup` command tried to open a browser for authentication, but the process was terminated (likely because there's no interactive browser available in this context).\n\nThe output shows:\n- Step 1/6: gcloud CLI found ✓\n- Step 2/6: Not logged in. Running gcloud auth login...\n- Your browser has been opened to visit: [OAuth URL]\n- Process exited with signal SIGTERM\n\nThe browser was supposed to open for OAuth authentication, but the process was terminated. This is because I'm running in a non-interactive environment where a browser can't be opened automatically.\n\nI need to use the browser tool to complete this OAuth flow. The URL is:\nhttps://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/auth?response_type=code&client_id=32555940559.apps.googleusercontent.com&redirect_uri=http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A8085%2F&scope=openid+https%3A%2F%2Fwww.googleapis.com%2Fauth%2Fuserinfo.email+https%3A%2F%2Fwww.googleapis.com%2Fauth%2Fcloud-platform+https%3A%2F%2Fwww.googleapis.com%2Fauth%2Fappengine.admin+https%3A%2F%2Fwww.googleapis.com%2Fauth%2Fsqlservice.login+https%3A%2F%2Fwww.googleapis.com%2Fauth%2Fcompute+https%3A%2F%2Fwww.googleapis.com%2Fauth%2Faccounts.reauth&state=a0faWUuS2I7Jhl95n38FJ1adWNzQVY&access_type=offline&code_challenge=wL1FOI5Halhn4FwQmC_gCa--NFA4XjE-18e87teuZSY&code_challenge_method=S256\n\nHowever, this URL uses localhost:8085 as the redirect URI, which means the browser needs to be able to communicate back to the local machine. This might not work with the browser tool.\n\nLet me try a different approach. I should report this to the user and explain the situation. The OAuth flow requires interactive browser access, which is difficult to automate.\n\nAlternatively, I could try using the browser tool to complete the authentication, but I need to:\n1. Navigate to the OAuth URL\n2. Sign in with the credentials (kublai@kurult.ai / WH@JRB6V67Yue39EcBqt3t)\n3. Authorize the application\n4. The redirect should go to localhost:8085 which gcloud is listening on\n\nLet me try using the browser tool to complete this flow.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The user has provided me with Google Workspace credentials for Kublai and wants me to set up Google Workspace using CLI. I've already saved the credentials to a secure file.\n\nThe `gws auth setup` command tried to open a browser for authentication, but the process was terminated (likely because there's no interactive browser available in this context).\n\nThe OAuth flow requires interactive browser access. The URL is:\n```\nhttps://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/auth?response_type=code&client_id=32555940559.apps.googleusercontent.com&redirect_uri=http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A8085%2F&scope=...\n```\n\nHowever, this uses localhost:8085 as the redirect URI, which means the browser needs to communicate back to the local machine.\n\nLet me try using the browser tool to complete this authentication flow. I'll:\n1. Start the gcloud auth login process in the background\n2. Use the browser tool to complete the OAuth flow\n3. Sign in with the Kublai credentials\n\nLet me try this approach:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_842d17ae0a8b442c8bd28baa","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"export PATH=/opt/homebrew/share/google-cloud-sdk/bin:\"$PATH\" && gcloud auth login --no-launch-browser 2>&1 &\nsleep 2\necho \"gcloud auth login started\"","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":99009,"output":896,"cacheRead":37184,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":137089,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772729679385}}
