{"type":"message","id":"5b4d2a92","parentId":"27bc135e","timestamp":"2026-03-05T16:55:57.605Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user has provided me with Google Workspace credentials for Kublai and wants me to set up Google Workspace using CLI. I've already saved the credentials to a secure file.\n\nThe `gcloud auth login --no-launch-browser` command showed the OAuth URL but then crashed because it couldn't read input (EOFError). The URL is:\n\n```\nhttps://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/auth?response_type=code&client_id=32555940559.apps.googleusercontent.com&redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fsdk.cloud.google.com%2Fauthcode.html&scope=openid+https%3A%2F%2Fwww.googleapis.com%2Fauth%2Fuserinfo.email+https%3A%2F%2Fwww.googleapis.com%2Fauth%2Fcloud-platform+https%3A%2F%2Fwww.googleapis.com%2Fauth%2Fappengine.admin+https%3A%2F%2Fwww.googleapis.com%2Fauth%2Fsqlservice.login+https%3A%2F%2Fwww.googleapis.com%2Fauth%2Fcompute+https%3A%2F%2Fwww.googleapis.com%2Fauth%2Faccounts.reauth&state=7pILVtEEtVJ7X4orBhGTbNds2avvDl&prompt=consent&token_usage=remote&access_type=offline&code_challenge=Qp_ubHzQM-jMBd_e50KrwmZjV6zOlMRtgF5lx0KFA2E&code_challenge_method=S256\n```\n\nThe redirect_uri is `https://sdk.cloud.google.com/authcode.html` which is different from the previous one (localhost:8085). This is an easier redirect to handle because it's a web URL, not localhost.\n\nThe flow should be:\n1. Navigate to the OAuth URL in the browser\n2. Sign in with kublai@kurult.ai / WH@JRB6V67Yue39EcBqt3t\n3. Authorize the application\n4. Get redirected to https://sdk.cloud.google.com/authcode.html?code=...\n5. Extract the code from the URL\n6. Pass the code back to gcloud\n\nLet me try using the browser tool to complete this flow. I'll use the chrome profile to navigate to the OAuth URL.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The user has provided me with Google Workspace credentials for Kublai and wants me to set up Google Workspace using CLI. I've al