{"type":"message","id":"33a83838","parentId":"c48ac61e","timestamp":"2026-03-05T16:56:45.625Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The user has provided me with Google Workspace credentials for Kublai and wants me to set up Google Workspace using CLI. I've already:\n\n1. ✅ Saved the credential securely to `/Users/kublai/.openclaw/credentials/google-kublai.env`\n2. ✅ Confirmed gws CLI is installed (version 0.3.5)\n3. ✅ Installed Google Cloud SDK (version 559.0.0)\n\nHowever, the authentication setup has encountered issues:\n- The browser tool is returning 404 errors when trying to open Google OAuth pages\n- gcloud/gws auth requires interactive browser access for OAuth flow\n\nThe OAuth flow requires:\n1. Navigate to the Google OAuth URL\n2. Sign in with kublai@kurult.ai / WH@JRB6V67Yue39EcBqt3t\n3. Authorize the application\n4. Get the verification code\n5. Pass it back to gcloud/gws\n\nThe browser tool cannot access Google's OAuth pages directly. This is a limitation.\n\nI should report the current status to the user and provide alternative options. Let me summarize what's been done and what needs to happen next.**Status Report - Google Workspace Setup for Kublai**\n\nI've successfully completed the initial setup:\n\n| Task | Status |\n|------|--------|\n| **Credential saved** | ✅ `/Users/kublai/.openclaw/credentials/google-kublai.env` |\n| **gws CLI** | ✅ Installed (version 0.3.5) |\n| **Google Cloud SDK** | ✅ Installed (version 559.0.0) |\n| **OAuth Authentication** | ⚠️ **Blocked - Browser tool limitation** |\n\n---\n\n**The Issue:**\n\nThe gws/gcloud OAuth flow requires interactive browser access to:\n1. Navigate to Google's OAuth page\n2. Sign in with kublai@kurult.ai credentials\n3. Authorize the application\n4. Complete the authentication flow\n\nThe OpenClaw browser tool returns **HTTP 404** when accessing Google OAuth pages, which prevents automated authentication.\n\n---\n\n**What Needs to Happen:**\n\n**Option 1: Manual Authentication (Recommended)**\nYou'll need to run this manually in your terminal:\n```bash\n# Add gcloud to PATH\nexport PATH=/opt/homebrew/share/google-cloud-sdk/bin:\"$PATH\"\n\n# Authenticate (this will open a browser)\ngcloud auth login\n\n# Then continue with gws setup\ngws auth setup\ngws auth login\n```\n\n**Option 2: Service Account**\nYou could create a Google Cloud service account for Kublai and provide me with the service account JSON file. This would avoid the OAuth browser flow.\n\n**Option 3: Pre-configured Client Secrets**\nIf you have a `client_secret.json` file from Google Cloud Console, I could use that instead.\n\n---\n\n**Current Status:**\n- ✅ All CLI tools installed\n- ✅ Credentials saved securely\n- ⚠️ Awaiting authentication to complete setup\n\nWould you like me to proceed with a specific option, or would you prefer to complete the authentication manually?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-4.7","usage":{"input":135753,"output":652,"cacheRead":3328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":139733,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772729780444}}
