to error count exceeding threshold\n3. Note that core services are all operational\n4. This is not a critical issue\n\nAccording to HEARTBEAT.md:\n- \"If Something Needs Attention: Report what's blocked, which agent is affected, what decision/action is needed\"\n- \"If nothing urgent → respond `HEARTBEAT_OK`\"\n\nIs this \"urgent\"? The system is functional - all core services are up. The degraded status is just due to log noise. I should report this but it's not critical.\n\nActually, I think I should report this clearly but note that it's not critical. The system is operational.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**Error Investigation Results:**\n\nThe \"degraded\" status is due to error count crossing the 50-error threshold:\n\n| Time | Errors | Status |\n|------|--------|--------|\n| 12:30 | 23 | healthy |\n| 12:35 | 26 | healthy |\n| 12:40 | 34 | healthy |\n| 12:45 | 44 | healthy |\n| 12:50 | 49 | healthy |\n| 12:55 | 51 | **degraded** ⚠️ |\n| 13:00 | 51 | **degraded** ⚠️ |\n\n**Error Sources Identified:**\n\n1. **Multiple LaunchAgents detected:**\n   - com.kurultai.auto-dispatch\n   - com.kurultai.ogedei-watchdog  \n   - com.kurultai.task-watcher\n\n2. **Missing skill file:**\n   - `/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/skills/kurultai-reflection/SKILL.md` (ENOENT)\n\n3. **Gateway cleanup hints** (old plist files)\n\n**Actual System State:**\n- Gateway: UP ✅\n- Neo4j: UP ✅\n- Redis: UP ✅\n- Parse: 200 ✅\n- LLM Survivor: 200 ✅\n- No fatal errors\n\n**Assessment:** The \"degraded\" status is due to log noise (error count > 50 threshold), not actual service failures. All core services are operational. This is **not critical** - the system is functioning properly.\n\n**Recommended Action:** Investigate error sources during next maintenance window. No immediate action required.\n\n---\n\nSince core services are operational and this is log noise, not a functional issue:\n\nHEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5",