{"type":"message","id":"2b540049","parentId":"fe014cee","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:07:46.709Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to bring \"Parse for Agents\" to a state of production readiness. This is a direct instruction from the human operator.\n\nLooking at the context:\n1. Earlier today I tested Parse for Agents and found that /agents returns 404 - the feature wasn't built\n2. I created a task for Temujin to build it, which was executed but the feature still doesn't exist\n3. Danny asked me to have Temujin update the spec with injection detection, which was completed\n4. But the actual /agents frontend and API endpoints still return 404\n\nSo \"bring to production readiness\" means:\n1. Actually build the /agents frontend\n2. Actually build the /api/v1/agents-test/* API endpoints\n3. Deploy to production (parsethe.media)\n4. Ensure it's working and testable\n\nThis is a significant task. I need to:\n1. Understand what needs to be built (check the spec files)\n2. Route this to Temujin properly\n3. Monitor execution to ensure actual work is done\n4. Verify deployment\n\nLet me first check what the current state of the Parse for Agents codebase is, then create a comprehensive task for Temujin.\n\nActually, I should also consider: the task execution system was working earlier when Temujin updated the spec files. So I should be able to route this task properly.\n\nLet me:\n1. Check the current state of the Parse codebase\n2. Create a comprehensive task for Temujin to bring Parse for Agents to production readiness\n3. Monitor the execution","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The user is asking me to bring Parse for Agents to production readiness. This is a direct instruction from the human operator.\n\nEarlier today:\n- I tested /agents and it returned 404 - the feature wasn't built\n- I created a task for Temujin which was executed but the feature still doesn't exist\n- The spec files were updated with injection detection\n\nNow I need to actually get this feature built and deployed. Let me:\n1. Check the current state of the Parse codebase\n2. Create a comprehensive task for Temujin with clear production readiness criteria\n3. Monitor execution to ensure actual work is done\n\nLet me first check what exists in the Parse codebase:The user wants me to bring Parse for Agents to production readiness. This is a significant task that requires:\n1. Building the /agents frontend\n2. Building the /api/v1/agents-test/* API endpoints\n3. Deploying to production\n\nLet me first check the current state of the Parse codebase:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_76345c775aa14bd98673b5c3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/projects/parse-github/src/app/agents* 2>/dev/null | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fe9eccc1cf0d4fc5a0fb0366","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/projects/parse-github/src/app/api/v1/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b66fe663468644989517a44f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" https://www.parsethe.media/agents && echo \" /agents\" && curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" https://www.parsethe.media/api/v1/evaluate && echo \" /api/v1/evaluate\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":143507,"output":673,"cacheRead":3392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":147572,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772734037156}}
