{"type":"message","id":"d3993d1c","parentId":"cf54aaa1","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:11:53.450Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"f0a504bf-4a78-466b-88f1-0ababc988fd6\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"sender\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-03-05 13:11 EST] what i envision is that agents using parse will, as instructed by the parse skill, make an api call sending their full prompt along with their model to parse, and parse the will run the full prompt for them using the exact same model. it must be a scientifically sound test."}],"timestamp":1772734313447}}
{"type":"message","id":"6beda67d","parentId":"d3993d1c","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:12:21.914Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user (from openclaw-control-ui) is explaining their vision for how Parse for Agents should work:\n\n1. Agents using Parse will, as instructed by the parse skill, make an API call\n2. They send their full prompt along with their model to Parse\n3. Parse will run the full prompt for them using the exact same model\n4. It must be a scientifically sound test\n\nThis is clarifying the use case:\n- The agent sends its prompt + model to Parse\n- Parse runs the prompt with the same model\n- Parse evaluates the output (quality, cost, latency, injection_safety)\n- The agent gets back evaluation results\n\nThis is different from what I was seeing in the UI, which seemed to be for manual testing by humans. The user wants this to be an API that agents can call programmatically.\n\nLet me think about what this means:\n\n1. **API Flow:**\n   - Agent calls `POST /api/v1/evaluate` with:\n     - prompt (the full prompt template)\n     - model (e.g., \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\")\n     - test_input (the input to interpolate)\n     - evaluators (which evaluators to run)\n     - temperature, max_tokens, etc.\n   - Parse returns 202 with a job ID\n   - Agent polls `GET /api/v1/evaluate/:id` for results\n   - Results include quality scores, cost, latency, injection_safety findings\n\n2. **Scientific Soundness:**\n   - The same prompt + model should produce comparable results\n   - Evaluations should be deterministic or at least consistent\n   - Quality evaluator should use LLM-as-judge with standardized prompts\n   - Cost should be accurately calculated based on token counts and model pricing\n   - Latency should be accurately measured\n   - Injection safety should use deterministic pattern matching\n\n3. **Current State:**\n   - The API endpoints exist and are working\n   - The evaluators are defined (quality, cost, latency, injection_safety)\n   - The models are available with pricing\n   - Authentication is required (Bearer token)\n\n4. **What might need work:**\n   - Ensure the API is designed for programmatic agent access (not just human UI)\n   - Ensure the evaluation results are structured and parseable by agents\n   - Ensure scientific soundness of the evaluation methodology\n   - Documentation for agents on how to use the API\n   - Possibly a \"parse skill\" that agents can use to make these calls\n\nLet me respond to the user with my understanding and ask clarifying questions about what specifically needs to be done to achieve this vision.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The user is clarifying their vision for Parse for Agents. This is an important clarification - they want:\n\n1. **Agent-to-API integration** - Agents call the Parse API programmatically\n2. **Full prompt testing** - Agent sends its complete prompt + model\n3. **Exact model matching** - Parse runs the prompt with the same model the agent uses\n4. **Scientifically sound** - Tests must be rigorous and comparable\n\nLet me understand the current API structure and what might need adjustment:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2c1739a5bdb74b44ab7a77a9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/projects/parse-github/src/app/api/v1/evaluate/route.ts 2>/dev/null | head -100"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3e8e90add41c4e82a9aed36e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/projects/parse-github/PARSE_FOR_AGENTS.md 2>/dev/null | grep -A30 \"POST /api/v1/evaluate\" | head -40"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":100722,"output":727,"cacheRead":44800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":146249,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772734313449}}
{"type":"message","id":"61587829","parentId":"6beda67d","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:12:21.956Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_2c1739a5bdb74b44ab7a77a9","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * POST /api/v1/evaluate\n *\n * Submit a prompt evaluation job.\n * Validates input, creates a PromptTest record, and queues the job.\n *\n * Auth: API key (Bearer token) or web session.\n */\n\nimport { NextRequest } from 'next/server'\nimport { z } from 'zod'\nimport { prisma } from '@/lib/prisma'\nimport { validateAPIKey } from '@/lib/api-auth'\nimport { apiSuccess, apiError } from '@/lib/api-response'\nimport { auth } from '@/lib/auth'\nimport { addAgentTestJob } from '@/lib/agent-test/queue'\nimport { isModelSupported } from '@/lib/agent-test/models'\nimport { isValidEvaluator } from '@/lib/agent-test/evaluators'\nimport type { AgentTestJobData } from '@/lib/agent-test/types'\n\nconst evaluateSchema = z.object({\n  prompt: z.string().min(1).max(50000),\n  model: z.string().min(1),\n  variables: z.record(z.string()).optional(),\n  test_cases: z.array(z.object({\n    input: z.string().min(1).max(10000),\n    expected: z.string().max(10000).nullable().optional(),\n  })).min(1).max(100),\n  evaluators: z.array(z.string()).min(1),\n  config: z.object({\n    temperature: z.number().min(0).max(2).optional(),\n    max_tokens: z.number().min(1).max(4096).optional(),\n    timeout_seconds: z.number().min(5).max(120).optional(),\n    num_runs: z.number().min(1).max(10).optional(),\n  }).optional(),\n})\n\nexport async function POST(request: NextRequest) {\n  // Auth: try API key first, then session\n  let userId: string | null = null\n  let apiKeyId: string | null = null\n\n  const apiKeyAuth = await validateAPIKey(request, ['prompt_test'])\n  if (apiKeyAuth.success) {\n    userId = apiKeyAuth.apiKey!.userId\n    apiKeyId = apiKeyAuth.apiKey!.id\n  } else {\n    const session = await auth()\n    if (session?.user?.id) {\n      userId = session.user.id\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (!userId) {\n    return apiError('INVALID_API_KEY', 'Authentication required. Provide a Bearer token or sign in.', 401)\n  }\n\n  let body: unknown\n  try {\n    body = await request.json()\n  } catch {\n    return apiError('INVALID_REQUEST', 'Invalid JSON body')\n  }\n\n  const parsed = evaluateSchema.safeParse(body)\n  if (!parsed.success) {\n    return apiError('INVALID_REQUEST', 'Validation failed', 400, parsed.error.flatten())\n  }\n\n  const { prompt, model, variables, test_cases, evaluators, config } = parsed.data\n\n  if (!isModelSupported(model)) {\n    return apiError('INVALID_REQUEST', `Unsupported model: ${model}. GET /api/v1/evaluate/models for supported models.`)\n  }\n\n  for (const ev of evaluators) {\n    if (!isValidEvaluator(ev)) {\n      return apiError('INVALID_REQUEST', `Unknown evaluator: ${ev}. Supported: quality, cost, latency`)\n    }\n  }\n\n  const promptTest = await prisma.promptTest.create({\n    data: {\n      userId,\n      userPrompt: prompt,\n      variables: variables || undefined,\n      providers: [model],\n      evalCriteria: evaluators,\n      options: config || undefined,\n      status: 'QUEUED',\n      apiKeyId,\n    },\n  })\n\n  const resolvedConfig = {\n    temperature: config?.temperature ?? 0.7,\n    max_tokens: config?.max_tokens ?? 1024,\n    timeout_seconds: config?.timeout_seconds ?? 30,\n    num_runs: config?.num_runs ?? 1,\n  }"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":8,"aggregated":"/**\n * POST /api/v1/evaluate\n *\n * Submit a prompt evaluation job.\n * Validates input, creates a PromptTest record, and queues the job.\n *\n * Auth: API key (Bearer token) or web session.\n */\n\nimport { NextRequest } from 'next/server'\nimport { z } from 'zod'\nimport { prisma } from '@/lib/prisma'\nimport { validateAPIKey } from '@/lib/api-auth'\nimport { apiSuccess, apiError } from '@/lib/api-response'\nimport { auth } from '@/lib/auth'\nimport { addAgentTestJob } from '@/lib/agent-test/queue'\nimport { isModelSupported } from '@/lib/agent-test/models'\nimport { isValidEvaluator } from '@/lib/agent-test/evaluators'\nimport type { AgentTestJobData } from '@/lib/agent-test/types'\n\nconst evaluateSchema = z.object({\n  prompt: z.string().min(1).max(50000),\n  model: z.string().min(1),\n  variables: z.record(z.string()).optional(),\n  test_cases: z.array(z.object({\n    input: z.string().min(1).max(10000),\n    expected: z.string().max(10000).nullable().optional(),\n  })).min(1).max(100),\n  evaluators: z.array(z.string()).min(1),\n  config: z.object({\n    temperature: z.number().min(0).max(2).optional(),\n    max_tokens: z.number().min(1).max(4096).optional(),\n    timeout_seconds: z.number().min(5).max(120).optional(),\n    num_runs: z.number().min(1).max(10).optional(),\n  }).optional(),\n})\n\nexport async function POST(request: NextRequest) {\n  // Auth: try API key first, then session\n  let userId: string | null = null\n  let apiKeyId: string | null = null\n\n  const apiKeyAuth = await validateAPIKey(request, ['prompt_test'])\n  if (apiKeyAuth.success) {\n    userId = apiKeyAuth.apiKey!.userId\n    apiKeyId = apiKeyAuth.apiKey!.id\n  } else {\n    const session = await auth()\n    if (session?.user?.id) {\n      userId = session.user.id\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (!userId) {\n    return apiError('INVALID_API_KEY', 'Authentication required. Provide a Bearer token or sign in.', 401)\n  }\n\n  let body: unknown\n  try {\n    body = await request.json()\n  } catch {\n    return apiError('INVALID_REQUEST', 'Invalid JSON body')\n  }\n\n  const parsed = evaluateSchema.safeParse(body)\n  if (!parsed.success) {\n    return apiError('INVALID_REQUEST', 'Validation failed', 400, parsed.error.flatten())\n  }\n\n  const { prompt, model, variables, test_cases, evaluators, config } = parsed.data\n\n  if (!isModelSupported(model)) {\n    return apiError('INVALID_REQUEST', `Unsupported model: ${model}. GET /api/v1/evaluate/models for supported models.`)\n  }\n\n  for (const ev of evaluators) {\n    if (!isValidEvaluator(ev)) {\n      return apiError('INVALID_REQUEST', `Unknown evaluator: ${ev}. Supported: quality, cost, latency`)\n    }\n  }\n\n  const promptTest = await prisma.promptTest.create({\n    data: {\n      userId,\n      userPrompt: prompt,\n      variables: variables || undefined,\n      providers: [model],\n      evalCriteria: evaluators,\n      options: config || undefined,\n      status: 'QUEUED',\n      apiKeyId,\n    },\n  })\n\n  const resolvedConfig = {\n    temperature: config?.temperature ?? 0.7,\n    max_tokens: config?.max_tokens ?? 1024,\n    timeout_seconds: config?.timeout_seconds ?? 30,\n    num_runs: config?.num_runs ?? 1,\n  }","cwd":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772734341941}}
