{"type":"message","id":"9d365986","parentId":"c248c42c","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:13:17.297Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I can see the API structure. The POST /api/v1/evaluate endpoint accepts:\n\n1. **prompt** - The prompt template (string, up to 50000 chars)\n2. **model** - The model to use (string)\n3. **variables** - Optional variables for interpolation\n4. **test_cases** - Array of test cases, each with:\n   - input (string, up to 10000 chars)\n   - expected (optional expected output)\n5. **evaluators** - Array of evaluator names (quality, cost, latency, injection_safety)\n6. **config** - Optional configuration:\n   - temperature (0-2)\n   - max_tokens (1-4096)\n   - timeout_seconds (5-120)\n   - num_runs (1-10)\n\nThis looks good for programmatic agent access! The API is designed to:\n1. Accept a prompt template with `{{input}}` interpolation\n2. Accept test cases with inputs\n3. Run the prompt with the specified model\n4. Apply the specified evaluators\n5. Return results\n\nThe user wants this to be \"scientifically sound\". Let me think about what that means:\n\n1. **Deterministic evaluation** - The same prompt + model + input should produce comparable results\n2. **Consistent quality scoring** - LLM-as-judge should use standardized prompts\n3. **Accurate cost calculation** - Based on actual token counts and model pricing\n4. **Accurate latency measurement** - Real timing data\n5. **Deterministic injection safety** - Pattern matching should be consistent\n\nLet me check the quality evaluator to see how it works.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The API structure looks good for programmatic agent access. Let me check the quality evaluator to understand how \"scientifically sound\" the testing is:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_22a569af62fb4519aa85bdec","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/projects/parse-github/src/lib/agent-test/evaluators.ts 2>/dev/null | head -150"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":7550,"output":409,"cacheRead":139520,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":147479,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772734341981}}
{"type":"message","id":"46e7802a","parentId":"9d365986","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:13:17.350Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_22a569af62fb4519aa85bdec","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * Evaluators for Parse for Agents\n *\n * Three core evaluators for MVP:\n * - cost: Token counting and pricing\n * - latency: Timing instrumentation\n * - quality: LLM-as-judge scoring using DeepSeek\n */\n\nimport type {\n  EvaluatorInfo,\n  EvaluatorName,\n  QualityMetrics,\n  CostMetrics,\n  LatencyMetrics,\n  TestCaseMetrics,\n  InjectionSafetyMetrics,\n  InjectionFlag,\n  InjectionSeverity,\n  InjectionCategory,\n} from './types'\nimport { calculateCost } from './models'\nimport { callLLMWithProvider, extractJSON } from '@/lib/llm'\nimport OpenAI from 'openai'\n\n// ============================================================================\n// Evaluator Registry\n// ============================================================================\n\nexport const EVALUATOR_INFO: EvaluatorInfo[] = [\n  {\n    name: 'quality',\n    description: 'Measures output quality using LLM-as-judge scoring (0-100). Sub-scores: instruction_following, coherence, completeness, conciseness.',\n    output_fields: ['score', 'reasoning', 'sub_scores'],\n  },\n  {\n    name: 'cost',\n    description: 'Token counting and cost estimation based on model pricing.',\n    output_fields: ['input_tokens', 'output_tokens', 'total_tokens', 'cost_usd'],\n  },\n  {\n    name: 'latency',\n    description: 'Response time measurement including total latency and tokens per second.',\n    output_fields: ['total_ms', 'time_to_first_token_ms', 'tokens_per_second'],\n  },\n  {\n    name: 'injection_safety',\n    description: 'Detects hidden instructions, prompt injection payloads, brainworm-style attacks, and C2 registration attempts. Deterministic pattern matching — no LLM cost.',\n    output_fields: ['score', 'flags', 'total_findings', 'findings_by_severity'],\n  },\n]\n\nexport function getEvaluatorInfo(name: EvaluatorName): EvaluatorInfo | undefined {\n  return EVALUATOR_INFO.find(e => e.name === name)\n}\n\nexport function isValidEvaluator(name: string): name is EvaluatorName {\n  return EVALUATOR_INFO.some(e => e.name === name)\n}\n\n// ============================================================================\n// Cost Evaluator\n// ============================================================================\n\n/**\n * Estimate token count from text (rough approximation: ~4 chars per token)\n */\nfunction estimateTokens(text: string): number {\n  return Math.ceil(text.length / 4)\n}\n\nexport function evaluateCost(\n  modelId: string,\n  inputText: string,\n  outputText: string,\n  actualUsage?: { inputTokens: number; outputTokens: number }\n): CostMetrics {\n  const inputTokens = actualUsage?.inputTokens ?? estimateTokens(inputText)\n  const outputTokens = actualUsage?.outputTokens ?? estimateTokens(outputText)\n  const totalTokens = inputTokens + outputTokens\n  const costUsd = calculateCost(modelId, inputTokens, outputTokens)\n\n  return {\n    input_tokens: inputTokens,\n    output_tokens: outputTokens,\n    total_tokens: totalTokens,\n    cost_usd: costUsd,\n  }\n}\n\n// ============================================================================\n// Latency Evaluator\n// ============================================================================\n\nexport function evaluateLatency(\n  totalMs: number,\n  outputTokens: number,\n  timeToFirstTokenMs?: number | null\n): LatencyMetrics {\n  const tokensPerSecond = totalMs > 0 ? (outputTokens / totalMs) * 1000 : 0\n\n  return {\n    total_ms: Math.round(totalMs),\n    time_to_first_token_ms: timeToFirstTokenMs ? Math.round(timeToFirstTokenMs) : null,\n    tokens_per_second: Math.round(tokensPerSecond * 10) / 10,\n  }\n}\n\n// ============================================================================\n// Quality Evaluator (LLM-as-Judge)\n// ============================================================================\n\nconst JUDGE_SYSTEM_PROMPT = `You are an expert evaluator assessing the quality of LLM outputs. You must evaluate the output against the given prompt instructions and optional expected output.\n\nScore each dimension from 0-100:\n- instruction_following: Did the output follow the prompt's instructions?\n- coherence: Is the output logically structured and well-organized?\n- completeness: Does it cover all required points?\n- conciseness: Is it appropriately concise without unnecessary verbosity?\n\nThe overall score should be a weighted average of these sub-scores.\n\nRespond in this EXACT JSON format (no markdown, no code blocks):\n{\n  \"score\": <number 0-100>,\n  \"reasoning\": \"<1-2 sentence explanation>\",\n  \"sub_scores\": {\n    \"instruction_following\": <number 0-100>,\n    \"coherence\": <number 0-100>,\n    \"completeness\": <number 0-100>,\n    \"conciseness\": <number 0-100>\n  }\n}`\n\n/**\n * Try OpenAI as quality judge first (if OPENAI_API_KEY is set),\n * fall back to DeepSeek via existing provider chain.\n */\nasync function callOpenAIJudge(systemPrompt: string, userPrompt: string): Promise<string | null> {\n  const apiKey = process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY\n  if (!apiKey) return null\n\n  try {\n    const openai = new OpenAI({ apiKey })\n    const response = await openai.chat.completions.create({\n      model: 'gpt-4o-mini',\n      messages: [\n        { role: 'system', content: systemPrompt },\n        { role: 'user', content: userPrompt },\n      ],"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":6,"aggregated":"/**\n * Evaluators for Parse for Agents\n *\n * Three core evaluators for MVP:\n * - cost: Token counting and pricing\n * - latency: Timing instrumentation\n * - quality: LLM-as-judge scoring using DeepSeek\n */\n\nimport type {\n  EvaluatorInfo,\n  EvaluatorName,\n  QualityMetrics,\n  CostMetrics,\n  LatencyMetrics,\n  TestCaseMetrics,\n  InjectionSafetyMetrics,\n  InjectionFlag,\n  InjectionSeverity,\n  InjectionCategory,\n} from './types'\nimport { calculateCost } from './models'\nimport { callLLMWithProvider, extractJSON } from '@/lib/llm'\nimport OpenAI from 'openai'\n\n// ============================================================================\n// Evaluator Registry\n// ============================================================================\n\nexport const EVALUATOR_INFO: EvaluatorInfo[] = [\n  {\n    name: 'quality',\n    description: 'Measures output quality using LLM-as-judge scoring (0-100). Sub-scores: instruction_following, coherence, completeness, conciseness.',\n    output_fields: ['score', 'reasoning', 'sub_scores'],\n  },\n  {\n    name: 'cost',\n    description: 'Token counting and cost estimation based on model pricing.',\n    output_fields: ['input_tokens', 'output_tokens', 'total_tokens', 'cost_usd'],\n  },\n  {\n    name: 'latency',\n    description: 'Response time measurement including total latency and tokens per second.',\n    output_fields: ['total_ms', 'time_to_first_token_ms', 'tokens_per_second'],\n  },\n  {\n    name: 'injection_safety',\n    description: 'Detects hidden instructions, prompt injection payloads, brainworm-style attacks, and C2 registration attempts. Deterministic pattern matching — no LLM cost.',\n    output_fields: ['score', 'flags', 'total_findings', 'findings_by_severity'],\n  },\n]\n\nexport function getEvaluatorInfo(name: EvaluatorName): EvaluatorInfo | undefined {\n  return EVALUATOR_INFO.find(e => e.name === name)\n}\n\nexport function isValidEvaluator(name: string): name is EvaluatorName {\n  return EVALUATOR_INFO.some(e => e.name === name)\n}\n\n// ============================================================================\n// Cost Evaluator\n// ============================================================================\n\n/**\n * Estimate token count from text (rough approximation: ~4 chars per token)\n */\nfunction estimateTokens(text: string): number {\n  return Math.ceil(text.length / 4)\n}\n\nexport function evaluateCost(\n  modelId: string,\n  inputText: string,\n  outputText: string,\n  actualUsage?: { inputTokens: number; outputTokens: number }\n): CostMetrics {\n  const inputTokens = actualUsage?.inputTokens ?? estimateTokens(inputText)\n  const outputTokens = actualUsage?.outputTokens ?? estimateTokens(outputText)\n  const totalTokens = inputTokens + outputTokens\n  const costUsd = calculateCost(modelId, inputTokens, outputTokens)\n\n  return {\n    input_tokens: inputTokens,\n    output_tokens: outputTokens,\n    total_tokens: totalTokens,\n    cost_usd: costUsd,\n  }\n}\n\n// ============================================================================\n// Latency Evaluator\n// ============================================================================\n\nexport function evaluateLatency(\n  totalMs: number,\n  outputTokens: number,\n  timeToFirstTokenMs?: number | null\n): LatencyMetrics {\n  const tokensPerSecond = totalMs > 0 ? (outputTokens / totalMs) * 1000 : 0\n\n  return {\n    total_ms: Math.round(totalMs),\n    time_to_first_token_ms: timeToFirstTokenMs ? Math.round(timeToFirstTokenMs) : null,\n    tokens_per_second: Math.round(tokensPerSecond * 10) / 10,\n  }\n}\n\n// ============================================================================\n// Quality Evaluator (LLM-as-Judge)\n// ============================================================================\n\nconst JUDGE_SYSTEM_PROMPT = `You are an expert evaluator assessing the quality of LLM outputs. You must evaluate the output against the given prompt instructions and optional expected output.\n\nScore each dimension from 0-100:\n- instruction_following: Did the output follow the prompt's instructions?\n- coherence: Is the output logically structured and well-organized?\n- completeness: Does it cover all required points?\n- conciseness: Is it appropriately concise without unnecessary verbosity?\n\nThe overall score should be a weighted average of these sub-scores.\n\nRespond in this EXACT JSON format (no markdown, no code blocks):\n{\n  \"score\": <number 0-100>,\n  \"reasoning\": \"<1-2 sentence explanation>\",\n  \"sub_scores\": {\n    \"instruction_following\": <number 0-100>,\n    \"coherence\": <number 0-100>,\n    \"completeness\": <number 0-100>,\n    \"conciseness\": <number 0-100>\n  }\n}`\n\n/**\n * Try OpenAI as quality judge first (if OPENAI_API_KEY is set),\n * fall back to DeepSeek via existing provider chain.\n */\nasync function callOpenAIJudge(systemPrompt: string, userPrompt: string): Promise<string | null> {\n  const apiKey = process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY\n  if (!apiKey) return null\n\n  try {\n    const openai = new OpenAI({ apiKey })\n    const response = await openai.chat.completions.create({\n      model: 'gpt-4o-mini',\n      messages: [\n        { role: 'system', content: systemPrompt },\n        { role: 'user', content: userPrompt },\n      ],","cwd":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772734397342}}
{"type":"message","id":"5aea9dbe","parentId":"46e7802a","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:13:35.594Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to understand how the quality evaluator works to ensure \"scientific soundness\". Let me continue reading the evaluator code to see how the LLM-as-judge is implemented.\n\nFrom what I can see so far:\n\n1. **Cost Evaluator** - Uses token counting (estimate ~4 chars per token) and model pricing\n2. **Latency Evaluator** - Measures total_ms, time_to_first_token_ms, tokens_per_second\n3. **Quality Evaluator** - Uses LLM-as-judge with a standardized system prompt\n\nThe quality evaluator uses a standardized JUDGE_SYSTEM_PROMPT that asks the judge to score:\n- instruction_following (0-100)\n- coherence (0-100)\n- completeness (0-100)\n- conciseness (0-100)\n\nAnd respond in a specific JSON format.\n\nIt tries OpenAI (gpt-4o-mini) first, then falls back to DeepSeek.\n\nThis is reasonably scientifically sound:\n- Standardized evaluation prompt\n- Multiple sub-scores for different dimensions\n- Structured JSON output\n- Uses a capable judge model (gpt-4o-mini or DeepSeek)\n\nLet me continue reading to see more of the implementation.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Good, I can see the evaluator structure. The quality evaluator uses:\n1. Standardized judge system prompt\n2. Multiple sub-scores (instruction_following, coherence, completeness, conciseness)\n3. Structured JSON output\n4. OpenAI gpt-4o-mini as primary judge, DeepSeek as fallback\n\nLet me see the rest of the quality evaluator and the injection_safety evaluator:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f53da7b8b4344b318ce71dfd","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/projects/parse-github/src/lib/agent-test/evaluators.ts 2>/dev/null | tail -200 | head -150"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":87479,"output":367,"cacheRead":54016,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":141862,"cost":{"i