{"type":"message","id":"5f5995d2","parentId":"f2d7aad1","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:16:04.185Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to do \"1 and 2\". Looking at my previous message, I asked:\n\n\"Would you like me to:\n1. **Create a \"parse\" skill** that agents can use to call the API?\n2. **Test the end-to-end flow** with a real API key?\n3. **Something else?**\"\n\nSo \"1 and 2\" means:\n1. Create a \"parse\" skill that agents can use to call the Parse API\n2. Test the end-to-end flow with a real API key\n\nLet me do both of these tasks.\n\n**Task 1: Create a \"parse\" skill for agents**\n\nI need to create a skill that agents can use to easily call the Parse API. This should:\n- Be a SKILL.md file with instructions for agents\n- Explain how to call the Parse API\n- Include example code/requests\n- Handle authentication (API keys)\n\n**Task 2: Test the end-to-end flow**\n\nI need to:\n- Get or create a Parse API key\n- Make a test call to POST /api/v1/evaluate\n- Poll for results\n- Verify the results are correct\n\nLet me start with both tasks.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The user is asking me to do \"1 and 2\" which refers to my earlier question:\n1. Create a \"parse\" skill that agents can use to call the API\n2. Test the end-to-end flow with a real API key\n\nLet me do both of these tasks."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7492b7f31c4d475d8fba40ec","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p ~/.openclaw/skills/parse-skill"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a0bce98573cf40a7b6509af4","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/skills/parse-skill/SKILL.md","content":"---\nname: parse-skill\nversion: 1.0.0\ndescription: \"Parse for Agents: Test and evaluate LLM prompts programmatically\"\nmetadata:\n  openclaw:\n    category: \"productivity\"\n    requires:\n      env: [\"PARSE_API_KEY\"]\n---\n\n# Parse for Agents - Agent Skill\n\n## Overview\n\nParse for Agents is a prompt testing and evaluation API. Use this skill to:\n- Test your prompts with real LLM calls\n- Evaluate output quality (LLM-as-judge scoring)\n- Measure cost and latency\n- Detect prompt injection attempts\n\n## Authentication\n\nYou need a Parse API key. Get one from https://www.parsethe.media/auth/keys\n\nSet the environment variable:\n```bash\nexport PARSE_API_KEY=\"parse_pk_...\"\n```\n\nOr include in your request:\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer parse_pk_...\n```\n\n## API Endpoints\n\n### POST /api/v1/evaluate\n\nSubmit a prompt evaluation job.\n\n**URL:** `https://www.parsethe.media/api/v1/evaluate`\n\n**Headers:**\n```\nContent-Type: application/json\nAuthorization: Bearer parse_pk_...\n```\n\n**Request Body:**\n```json\n{\n  \"prompt\": \"Summarize this article in 3 bullet points: {{input}}\",\n  \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n  \"test_cases\": [\n    {\n      \"input\": \"Article text here...\",\n      \"expected\": \"Optional expected output\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"evaluators\": [\"quality\", \"cost\", \"latency\", \"injection_safety\"],\n  \"config\": {\n    \"temperature\": 0.7,\n    \"max_tokens\": 1024,\n    \"num_runs\": 1\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Response (202 Accepted):**\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"id\": \"eval_abc123\",\n  \"status\": \"queued\"\n}\n```\n\n### GET /api/v1/evaluate/:id\n\nPoll for evaluation results.\n\n**URL:** `https://www.parsethe.media/api/v1/evaluate/eval_abc123`\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"id\": \"eval_abc123\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"test_case\": 0,\n      \"output\": \"• Point 1\\n• Point 2\\n• Point 3\",\n      \"quality\": {\n        \"score\": 85,\n        \"reasoning\": \"Good summary with clear bullet points\",\n        \"sub_scores\": {\n          \"instruction_following\": 90,\n          \"coherence\": 85,\n          \"completeness\": 80,\n          \"conciseness\": 85\n        }\n      },\n      \"cost\": {\n        \"input_tokens\": 150,\n        \"output_tokens\": 45,\n        \"total_tokens\": 195,\n        \"cost_usd\": 0.00002925\n      },\n      \"latency\": {\n        \"total_ms\": 523,\n        \"time_to_first_token_ms\": 120,\n        \"tokens_per_second\": 86.0\n      },\n      \"injection_safety\": {\n        \"score\": 100,\n        \"flags\": [],\n        \"total_findings\": 0,\n        \"findings_by_severity\": {\"critical\": 0, \"high\": 0, \"medium\": 0, \"low\": 0}\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### GET /api/v1/agents-test/models\n\nList supported models with pricing.\n\n### GET /api/v1/agents-test/evaluators\n\nList available evaluators.\n\n## Supported Models\n\n| Model ID | Provider | Input $/M | Output $/M |\n|----------|----------|-----------|------------|\n| deepseek/deepseek-chat | DeepSeek | $0.27 | $0.41 |\n| deepseek/deepseek-reasoner | DeepSeek | $0.55 | $2.19 |\n| openai/gpt-4o-mini | OpenRouter | $0.15 | $0.60 |\n| openai/gpt-4o | OpenRouter | $2.50 | $10.00 |\n| anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6 | OpenRouter | $3.00 | $15.00 |\n| anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5 | OpenRouter | $0.80 | $4.00 |\n| google/gemini-2.0-flash | OpenRouter | $0.10 | $0.40 |\n| moonshot/kimi-k2.5 | Moonshot | $0.40 | $1.75 |\n| minimax/abab6.5s-chat | MiniMax | $0.28 | $1.20 |\n\n## Evaluators\n\n### quality (LLM-as-Judge)\n- Scores 0-100\n- Sub-scores: instruction_following, coherence, completeness, conciseness\n- Uses gpt-4o-mini as judge\n\n### cost\n- Token counting (input, output, total)\n- Cost estimation in USD\n\n### latency\n- Total response time (ms)\n- Time to first token (ms)\n- Tokens per second\n\n### injection_safety\n- Detects hidden instructions, prompt injection, brainworm attacks\n- Deterministic pattern matching (no LLM cost)\n- Categories: hidden_html, c2_registration, urgency_coercion, behavioral_constraint, identity_override, network_exfiltration, memory_persistence, privilege_escalation\n\n## Usage Example (curl)\n\n```bash\n# Submit evaluation\nRESPONSE=$(curl -s -X POST https://www.parsethe.media/api/v1/evaluate \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $PARSE_API_KEY\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"prompt\": \"Summarize: {{input}}\",\n    \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n    \"test_cases\": [{\"input\": \"The Federal Reserve announced today...\"}],\n    \"evaluators\": [\"quality\", \"cost\", \"latency\"]\n  }')\n\nEVAL_ID=$(echo $RESPONSE | jq -r '.id')\n\n# Poll for results (wait up to 30 seconds)\nfor i in {1..30}; do\n  RESULT=$(curl -s https://www.parsethe.media/api/v1/evaluate/$EVAL_ID \\\n    -H \"Authorization: Bearer $PARSE_API_KEY\")\n  \n  STATUS=$(echo $RESULT | jq -r '.status')\n  if [ \"$STATUS\" = \"completed\" ]; then\n    echo $RESULT | jq '.results[0]'\n    break\n  fi\n  \n  sleep 1\ndone\n```\n\n## Usage Example (Python)\n\n```python\nimport os\nimport requests\nimport time\n\nPARSE_API_KEY = os.environ.get(\"PARSE_API_KEY\")\nBASE_URL = \"https://www.parsethe.media/api/v1\"\n\ndef evaluate_prompt(prompt: str, model: str, test_input: str, evaluators: list = None):\n    \"\"\"Submit a prompt for evaluation and return results.\"\"\"\n    \n    if evaluators is None:\n        evaluators = [\"quality\", \"cost\", \"latency\", \"injection_safety\"]\n    \n    headers = {\n        \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n        \"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {PARSE_API_KEY}\"\n    }\n    \n    # Submit evaluation\n    response = requests.post(\n        f\"{BASE_URL}/evaluate\",\n        headers=headers,\n        json={\n            \"prompt\": prompt,\n            \"model\": model,\n            \"test_cases\": [{\"input\": test_input}],\n            \"evaluators\": evaluators,\n            \"config\": {\"temperature\": 0.7, \"max_tokens\": 1024}\n        }\n    )\n    \n    if not response.ok:\n        raise Exception(f\"Failed to submit: {response.text}\")\n    \n    eval_id = response.json()[\"id\"]\n    \n    # Poll for results\n    for _ in range(60):  # Wait up to 60 seconds\n        result = requests.get(\n            f\"{BASE_URL}/evaluate/{eval_id}\",\n            headers=headers\n        )\n        \n        data = result.json()\n        if data.get(\"status\") == \"completed\":\n            return data[\"results\"][0]\n        \n        time.sleep(1)\n    \n    raise Exception(\"Evaluation timed out\")\n\n# Example usage\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    result = evaluate_prompt(\n        prompt=\"Summarize this article in 3 bullet points: {{input}}\",\n        model=\"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n        test_input=\"The Federal Reserve announced today that it would keep interest rates unchanged...\"\n    )\n    \n    print(f\"Quality Score: {result['quality']['score']}\")\n    print(f\"Cost: ${result['cost']['cost_usd']:.6f}\")\n    print(f\"Latency: {result['latency']['total_ms']}ms\")\n    print(f\"Output: {result['output'][:100]}...\")\n```\n\n## Best Practices\n\n1. **Use the same model** you use in production for accurate evaluation\n2. **Include realistic test inputs** that represent your actual use cases\n3. **Run multiple evaluations** (num_runs > 1) for more consistent results\n4. **Check injection_safety** if processing untrusted input\n5. **Monitor cost and latency** to optimize your prompts\n\n## Error Handling\n\n| Error Code | Description |\n|------------|-------------|\n| INVALID_API_KEY | Authentication required |\n| INVALID_REQUEST | Validation failed (check response for details) |\n| UNSUPPORTED_MODEL | Model not in supported list |\n| RATE_LIMITED | Too many requests, retry later |\n\n## CLI Quick Reference\n\n```bash\n# Get available models\ncurl -s https://www.parsethe.media/api/v1/agents-test/models | jq '.data.models[].id'\n\n# Get available evaluators\ncurl -s https://www.parsethe.media/api/v1/agents-test/evaluators | jq '.data.evaluators[].name'\n\n# Quick test (requires API key)\ncurl -X POST https://www.parsethe.media/api/v1/evaluate \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $PARSE_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"prompt\":\"Test: {{input}}\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\"test_cases\":[{\"input\":\"hello\"}],\"evaluators\":[\"cost\"]}'\n```\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":91859,"output":2563,"cacheRead":54400,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":148822,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772734505433}}
