{"type":"message","id":"637809ab","parentId":"f0763d0a","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:19:16.212Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user clicked \"Continue\" on the Google OAuth consent screen, but now we're back at the Parse sign-in page. The URL changed back to \"https://www.parsethe.media/auth/signin\".\n\nThis is strange. The OAuth flow should have redirected to Parse with the authorization code, which would then complete the sign-in and redirect to the main page or dashboard.\n\nThe fact that we're back at the sign-in page suggests:\n1. The OAuth flow failed\n2. The redirect didn't work properly\n3. There was an error in the authentication callback\n\nLet me check if there's an error message or if we need to try a different approach.\n\nActually, looking at the snapshot, it's the same sign-in page as before. The navigation still shows \"Sign In\" and \"Subscribe\" links, which means we're not signed in yet.\n\nLet me try to navigate to the /agents page directly to see if we're actually signed in, or check if there's an error.\n\nActually, let me try clicking \"Continue with Google\" again to see if the OAuth flow works this time.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The user clicked \"Continue\" on the Google OAuth consent screen, but now we're back at the Parse sign-in page. The URL changed back to \"https://www.parsethe.media/auth/signin\".\n\nThis is strange. The OAuth flow should have redirected to Parse with the authorization code and completed the sign-in. Let me check if we're actually signed in by navigating to the /agents page or the API keys page:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ed99022c0d414a628ff66ba6","name":"browser","arguments":{"action":"navigate","url":"https://www.parsethe.media/auth/keys","targetId":"6184D414BDEBCEA6CDA0EF9002734742"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":81572,"output":363,"cacheRead":63872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":145807,"c