{"type":"message","id":"e7237cad","parentId":"a96f773b","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:19:48.848Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user navigated to the Parse API keys page (/auth/keys) but got a 404 error: \"This page could not be found.\"\n\nThe navigation still shows \"Sign In\" and \"Subscribe\" links, which means we're not signed in yet. The OAuth flow didn't complete successfully.\n\nThe issue is that /auth/keys returns 404 - this page might not exist or might require sign-in first.\n\nLet me try a different approach. I should:\n1. Go back to the sign-in page\n2. Try the Google OAuth flow again\n3. Or try signing in with email/password using the Kublai Google account credentials\n\nActually, the Kublai Google account (kublai@kurult.ai) is a Google account, not a Parse account with email/password. So I need to use the \"Continue with Google\" button.\n\nLet me try the Google OAuth flow again and see if it works this time.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The user navigated to the Parse API keys page (/auth/keys) but got a 404 error: \"This page could not be found.\"\n\nThe navigation still shows \"Sign In\" and \"Subscribe\" links, which means we're not signed in yet. The OAuth flow didn't complete successfully.\n\nLet me try a different approach. I should:\n1. Go back to the sign-in page\n2. Try the Google OAuth flow again\n3. Or check if there's a different page for API keys\n\nLet me check what pages are available for authenticated users by looking at the Parse codebase.\n\nActually, looking at the situation more carefully:\n- The Google OAuth flow seemed to work (we got to the consent screen)\n- We clicked \"Continue\" to authorize\n- But then we got redirected back to the sign-in page\n- This suggests the OAuth callback might have failed\n\nThis could be because:\n1. The Kublai Google account is new and hasn't been registered with Parse yet\n2. There's an issue with the OAuth callback\n3. The user needs to sign up first (not sign in)\n\nLet me try going to the sign-up page instead.The user navigated to /auth/keys but got a 404 error. The navigation still shows \"Sign In\" and \"Subscribe\" links, which means we're not signed in yet.\n\nThe OAuth flow didn't complete successfully. Let me try the sign-up page instead, since the Kublai Google account might not be registered with Parse yet:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2ca7f132b5094a72a0e3dcea","name":"browser","arguments":{"action":"navigate","targetId":"6184D414BDEBCEA6CDA0EF9002734742","url":"https://www.parsethe.media/auth/signup"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":2071,"output":552,"cacheRead":144448,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":147071,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772734764984}}
