{"type":"message","id":"50090b6b","parentId":"4cfb4bc3","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:22:12.837Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user waited 3 seconds after clicking \"Continue\" on the Google OAuth consent screen, but we're back at the Parse sign-in page again. The URL changed back to \"https://www.parsethe.media/auth/signin\" and the navigation still shows \"Sign In\" and \"Subscribe\" links.\n\nThis is the same issue as before. The OAuth flow seems to be completing on Google's side, but the redirect back to Parse is not working properly.\n\nThis is taking too long. I've been trying to authenticate with Parse via Google OAuth for a while now, and it's not working. The user asked me to do two things:\n1. Create a \"parse\" skill - ✅ DONE\n2. Test the end-to-end flow with a real API key - ⚠️ BLOCKED by authentication issues\n\nI should report the status to the user:\n1. Task 1 is complete - I've created the parse-skill SKILL.md file\n2. Task 2 is blocked - The Google OAuth flow is not completing successfully\n\nThe issue is that the OAuth flow redirects back to the sign-in page instead of completing the authentication. This could be a browser automation issue or a Parse configuration issue.\n\nLet me report this to the user and suggest alternative approaches.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The user waited 3 seconds after clicking \"Continue\" on the Google OAuth consent screen, but we're back at the Parse sign-in page again. The OAuth flow is not completing successfully.\n\nThis is taking too long. Let me report the status to the user:\n\n**Task Status Report:**\n\n1. **Task 1: Create a \"parse\" skill** - ✅ **DONE**\n   - Created `/Users/kublai/.openclaw/skills/parse-skill/SKILL.md`\n   - Includes authentication instructions, API endpoints, usage examples (curl and Python)\n   - Documents all 9 supported models and 4 evaluators\n   - Ready for agents to use\n\n2. **Task 2: Test the end-to-end flow** - ⚠️ **