{"type":"message","id":"1aa780fb","parentId":"f5262c25","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:29:19.807Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The snapshot shows that the sign-in failed with an error message: \"Invalid email or password\". The page still shows the sign-in form with:\n- Email: kublai@kurult.ai (still filled in)\n- Password: WH@JRB6V67Yue39EcBqt3t (still filled in)\n- Error message: \"Invalid email or password\"\n- Success message: \"Account created successfully! Please sign in.\" (still showing)\n\nThis is strange because:\n1. The account was created successfully\n2. But the sign-in with the same credentials failed\n\nThis could mean:\n1. The password I used during sign-up was not the same as the one I'm using for sign-in (but I used the same password)\n2. There's a verification step required before sign-in\n3. The account creation didn't actually work as expected\n\nWait - looking at the snapshot more carefully, I see both messages:\n- \"Invalid email or password\" (error)\n- \"Account created successfully! Please sign in.\" (success)\n\nThis is confusing. The account was created, but the sign-in failed with \"Invalid email or password\".\n\nLet me think about this. The account was created with:\n- Name: Kublai Kurultai\n- Email: kublai@kurult.ai\n- Password: WH@JRB6V67Yue39EcBqt3t\n\nBut the sign-in failed with \"Invalid email or password\". This could be because:\n1. The account requires email verification before sign-in\n2. The password has special characters that are being handled differently\n3. There's a bug in the Parse authentication system\n\nThe password has special characters: WH@JRB6V67Yue39EcBqt3t\n- @ symbol\n- uppercase and lowercase letters\n- numbers\n\nMaybe the @ symbol is causing issues? Or maybe the account requires email verification?\n\nI should try a different approach. Let me check if there's a verification email or if I need to verify the email before signing in.\n\nActually, looking at the situation