{"type":"message","id":"9184496c","parentId":"a3a93256","timestamp":"2026-03-05T20:09:06.302Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Critical Finding!** These are NOT completed tasks - they're PENDING task definitions with misleading `.md.done` suffix. The files show `Status: PENDING` but the naming convention confuses the dispatch system.\n\nThis explains why:\n- I counted 11 \"pending\" files\n- Agents reported 0 pending according to tock\n- The dispatch system can't find work\n\nThe root cause is a **task file naming inconsistency** - task definitions have `.md.done` suffix which looks like \"completed\" to some scanners but \"pending\" to others.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Hourly Kurultai Reflection Complete - 3:08 PM EST**\n\n**Key Findings:**\n1. **Task naming crisis identified:** 11 pending tasks exist with confusing `.md.done` naming - dispatch can't route them properly\n2. **Fleet remains idle:** 9th+ hour of zero task completions across all 5 agents\n3. **Parse Conversion Alert failing:** Only cron with errors (consecutive_errors=1)\n4. **2 failed Jochi tasks:** error-baseline and queue-stall-analysis need retry\n5. **LLM timeouts:** Embedded run failed at 15:04\n\n**Immediate Actions Needed:**\n1. **CRITICAL:** Standardize task file naming (unblocks all 5 agents)\n2. **HIGH:** Investigate Parse Conversion Alert cron failure\n3. **HIGH:** Retry Jochi's 2 failed analysis tasks\n\n**Agent Grades:** Temujin (D), Mongke (D), Chagatai (C), Jochi (D+), Ogedei (D+)\n**System Grade:** D\n\nReport saved to: `/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/logs/reflections/2026-03-05-1503-hourly-reflection.md`"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772741346302}}
