nd design a pay-as-you-go system for Parse for Agents."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b26ddf0bccf9468e8ffb26ef","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"runtime":"acp","agentId":"claude","mode":"run","task":"Design and plan a payment system for \"Parse for Agents\" using the x402 protocol for pay-as-you-go billing.\n\n## Context\n- Parse for Agents is a prompt testing and evaluation API\n- x402 protocol is already mentioned in the codebase for payment integration\n- Agents should be able to pay per API call or per evaluation\n\n## Tasks\n1. Research the x402 protocol - find any documentation, implementation files, or references in the codebase\n   - Check /Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/ for x402 references\n   - Check ~/.openclaw/agents/main/ for any x402 documentation\n   - Search the web if needed for x402 protocol specifications\n\n2. Design the payment flow:\n   - How does an agent initiate a payment?\n   - How is payment verified before API execution?\n   - What's the pricing model (per call, per token, per evaluation)?\n   - How are payments tracked and reported?\n\n3. Plan the implementation:\n   - What changes are needed to the Parse for Agents API?\n   - What new endpoints or middleware are needed?\n   - How to integrate with existing auth system?\n\n4. Output a design document with:\n   - Architecture diagram (text-based)\n   - API changes required\n   - Implementation steps\n   - Pricing recommendations\n\n## Output Location\nSave the design document to: ~/.openclaw/agents/main/projects/parse-for-agents/x402-payment-design.md\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Clear understanding of x402 protocol documented\n- Payment flow designed with sequence diagram\n- Implementation plan with specific steps\n- Pricing model recommendation"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":2235,"output":787,"cacheRead":32832,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35854,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReas