{"type":"message","id":"024a28c4","parentId":"27fb7b44","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:52:16.096Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The sessions_send is restricted due to visibility settings. I can't steer the existing ACP session directly.\n\nThe user wants me to use horde-brainstorming in Claude Code. Since I can't steer the existing session, I should spawn a new session with the horde-brainstorming skill explicitly mentioned in the task.\n\nLet me spawn a new ACP session that explicitly uses /horde-brainstorming.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The existing session can't be steered due to visibility restrictions. Let me spawn a new session that explicitly uses horde-brainstorming from the start:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_036cff8ea7894ddbbe04aba0","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"agentId":"claude","mode":"run","runtime":"acp","task":"Use the /horde-brainstorming skill to design a payment system for \"Parse for Agents\" using the x402 protocol.\n\n## Apply Horde-Brainstorming Methodology\n\n### Phase 1: DIVERGE\nGenerate 5+ payment model options:\n- Per-call pricing (e.g., $0.01 per evaluation)\n- Per-token pricing (based on LLM usage)\n- Subscription tiers (monthly plans)\n- Credit packs (pre-purchased credits)\n- Hybrid models (base + usage)\n- Freemium (free tier + paid)\n\n### Phase 2: EVALUATE\nScore each option (1-10) against:\n1. Agent autonomy - Can agents pay without human intervention?\n2. Implementation simplicity - How complex to build?\n3. Revenue predictability - Consistent income?\n4. Fairness - Users pay for what they use?\n5. x402 compatibility - Works well with the protocol?\n\n### Phase 3: CONVERGE\n- Select the best approach\n- Design the payment flow\n- Create implementation plan\n\n## Context\n- Parse for Agents: prompt testing and evaluation API\n- x402 protocol: payment protocol for AI agents\n- Goal: Pay-as-you-go billing for autonomous agents\n\n## Research First\n- Search for x402 protocol documentation in /Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/\n- Check ~/.openclaw/agents/main/ for any x402 references\n- Web search if needed\n\n## Output\nSave design document to: ~/.openclaw/agents/main/projects/parse-for-agents/x402-payment-design.md\n\nInclude:\n- Diverge phase results (all options)\n- Evaluate phase scores (table format)\n- Converge phase decision (selected approach)\n- Architecture diagram (text-based)\n- Implementation steps\n- Pricing recommendation"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":967,"output":523,"cacheRead":36480,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37970,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772751121552}}
