{"type":"message","id":"c4f2bebf","parentId":"c2d53118","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:53:49.914Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clearer picture. Let me summarize what I found:\n\n1. **agents.json** - Lists all 6 agents with their configurations. All agents use the same model: `kimi-coding/k2p5`. There's no per-agent \"thinking\" or \"effort\" setting in this file.\n\n2. **Claude settings.json** - Shows:\n   - `\"alwaysThinkingEnabled\": true` - Thinking is always enabled\n   - `\"effortLevel\": \"high\"` - Effort level is set to high\n\n3. The agents.json doesn't have per-agent thinking/effort settings.\n\nSo the answer is:\n- The Claude Code sessions (ACP sessions) use the global settings from `~/.claude/settings.json`\n- These settings have `effortLevel: \"high\"` and `alwaysThinkingEnabled: true`\n- This applies to ALL agents when they spawn Claude Code sessions\n- The agents themselves (in agents.json) don't have individual thinking/effort settings\n\nI should also note that when spawning sessions via `sessions_spawn`, there's a `thinking` parameter that can override the default. But by default, all ACP sessions will use the high effort setting from the global config.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Here's what I found about the effort/thinking configuration:\n\n## Answer: Yes, all Claude Code sessions run with high effort\n\nThe configuration shows:\n\n### Global Claude Code Settings (`~/.claude/settings.json`)\n```\n\"alwaysThinkingEnabled\": true,\n\"effortLevel\": \"high\"\n```\n\n### Agents Configuration (`~/.openclaw/config/agents.json`)\n- All 6 agents use `kimi-coding/k2p5` model\n- No per-agent thinking/effort overrides\n- All agents inherit the global high effort setting\n\n### What This Means\n- **All ACP sessions** (Claude Code) spawned by any agent will use high effort\n- **Thinking is always enabled** for extended reasoning\n- The `sessions_spawn` tool can override this with the `thinking` parameter if needed\n\n### Per-Agent Customization\nIf you want different effort levels per agent, you could:\n1. Add a `thinking` field to each agent in `agents.json`\n2. Pass the `thinking` parameter when calling `sessions_spawn`\n3. Create agent-specific Claude settings files\n\nWould you like me to configure per-agent effort levels?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":1036,"output":490,"cacheRead":38592,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40118,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772751212191}}
{"type":"message","id":"b99d26b0","parentId":"c4f2bebf","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:53:50.506Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The user is asking about whether all agents' Claude Code sessions run with \"high effort\" (likely referring to the thinking/reasoning mode). Let me check the configuration to answer this question."}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772751230506}}
{"type":"message","id":"898c23a6","parentId":"b99d26b0","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:53:50.577Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's what I found about the effort/thinking configuration:\n\n## Answer: Yes, all Claude Code sessions run with high effort\n\nThe configuration shows:\n\n### Global Claude Code Settings (`~/.claude/settings.json`)\n```\n\"alwaysThinkingEnabled\": true,\n\"effortLevel\": \"high\"\n```\n\n### Agents Configuration (`~/.openclaw/config/agents.json`)\n- All 6 agents use `kimi-coding/k2p5` model\n- No per-agent thinking/effort overrides\n- All agents inherit the global high effort setting\n\n### What This Means\n- **All ACP sessions** (Claude Code) spawned by any agent will use high effort\n- **Thinking is always enabled** for extended reasoning\n- The `sessions_spawn` tool can override this with the `thinking` parameter if needed\n\n### Per-Agent Customization\nIf you want different effort levels per agent, you could:\n1. Add a `thinking` field to each agent in `agents.json`\n2. Pass the `thinking` parameter when calling `sessions_spawn`\n3. Create agent-specific Claude settings files\n\nWould you like me to configure per-agent effort levels?"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772751230577}}
{"type":"message","id":"6d73a2b4","parentId":"898c23a6","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:54:42.683Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"b10a53d8-8e88-4030-815e-bec6783a1805\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"sender\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-03-05 17:54 EST] what files can we edit so that each agent is instructed to prefer to use the horde skills by default when possible in claude code?"}],"timestamp":1772751282682}}
{"type":"message","id":"71712723","parentId":"6d73a2b4","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:54:59.915Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to know which files can be edited so that each agent is instructed to prefer using horde skills by default when possible in Claude Code.\n\nThis is a configuration question. I need to find where:\n1. Agent instructions/prompts are defined\n2. Claude Code skill preferences can be configured\n3. Per-agent settings can be customized\n\nLet me think about where these configurations might be:\n\n1. **AGENTS.md** - Each agent has an AGENTS.md file that defines their behavior\n2. **TOOLS.md** - Each agent has a TOOLS.md that defines tool usage\n3. **SOUL.md** - Core identity and NEVER rules\n4. **agents.json** - Agent configuration including model, workspace, etc.\n5. **~/.claude/settings.json** - Global Claude Code settings\n6. **Skill files** - SKILL.md files in skills directories\n\nThe user wants agents to prefer horde skills when spawning Claude Code sessions. This could be configured in:\n- Each agent's TOOLS.md (tool usage instructions)\n- Each agent's AGENTS.md (general behavior)\n- A system prompt or instruction file that gets passed to ACP sessions\n\nLet me check the relevant files to understand the structure and provide a clear answer.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The user wants to know which files to edit so that each agent prefers using horde skills by default when spawning Claude Code sessions. Let me check the relevant configuration files."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_af1ceae135d04cc1a2be91de","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== Main agent TOOLS.md (horde section) ===\" && grep -A 20 \"Horde Skills\" ~/.openclaw/agents/main/TOOLS.md 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a67947f48a3046df8d10b8a0","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== Claude Code wrapper ===\" && cat ~/.local/bin/claude-agent 2>/dev/null | head -50"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cf4541cf0dfd48f681540a79","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== Check for agent-specific Claude configs ===\" && ls -la ~/.claude/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5ad65f07352c411e80a0e02b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== Check agents.json structure for prompts ===\" && cat ~/.openclaw/config/agents.json 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":931,"output":445,"cacheRead":39616,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40992,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772751282683}}
{"type":"message","id":"b92d8ab1","parentId":"71712723","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:54:59.957Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_af1ceae135d04cc1a2be91de","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== Main agent TOOLS.md (horde section) ===\n### Horde Skills (Available in Claude Code Sessions)\nWhen invoking `claude-agent`, you can reference these skills in the prompt:\n\n**Orchestration:**\n- `/golden-horde` — 9 multi-agent patterns (review loop, debate, pipeline, etc.)\n- `/horde-swarm` — Parallel subagent dispatch (35+ agent types)\n- `/horde-brainstorming` — Structured ideation with diverge/evaluate/converge\n\n**Planning & Implementation:**\n- `/horde-plan` — Structured implementation plans with dependency tracking\n- `/horde-implement` — Execute plans with quality checkpoints\n- `/horde-gate-testing` — Integration tests between implementation phases\n\n**Quality:**\n- `/horde-review` — Multi-domain critical review (security, perf, architecture)\n- `/horde-test` — Parallel test suite execution\n- `/code-reviewer` — Automated code review\n\n**Specialist Skills:**\n- `/senior-architect`, `/senior-backend`, `/senior-frontend`, `/senior-devops`\n- `/senior-data-engineer`, `/senior-ml-engineer`, `/senior-data-scientist`"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":9,"aggregated":"=== Main agent TOOLS.md (horde section) ===\n### Horde Skills (Available in Claude Code Sessions)\nWhen invoking `claude-agent`, you can reference these skills in the prompt:\n\n**Orchestration:**\n- `/golden-horde` — 9 multi-agent patterns (review loop, debate, pipeline, etc.)\n- `/horde-swarm` — Parallel subagent dispatch (35+ agent types)\n- `/horde-brainstorming` — Structured ideation with diverge/evaluate/converge\n\n**Planning & Implementation:**\n- `/horde-plan` — Structured implementation plans with dependency tracking\n- `/horde-implement` — Execute plans with quality checkpoints\n- `/horde-gate-testing` — Integration tests between implementation phases\n\n**Quality:**\n- `/horde-review` — Multi-domain critical review (security, perf, architecture)\n- `/horde-test` — Parallel test suite execution\n- `/code-reviewer` — Automated code review\n\n**Specialist Skills:**\n- `/senior-architect`, `/senior-backend`, `/senior-frontend`, `/senior-devops`\n- `/senior-data-engineer`, `/senior-ml-engineer`, `/senior-data-scientist`","cwd":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772751299946}}
{"type":"message","id":"f848b546","parentId":"b92d8ab1","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:54:59.979Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a67947f48a3046df8d10b8a0","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== Claude Code wrapper ===\n#!/bin/bash\n# claude-agent: Wrapper for spawning Claude Code sessions from OpenClaw agents\n#\n# Handles:\n#   1. Strips CLAUDECODE env var (allows nested sessions)\n#   2. Adds --dangerously-skip-permissions (non-interactive)\n#   3. Uses default settings (all 23 plugins + 90+ skills)\n#   4. Configurable model\n#\n# Usage:\n#   claude-agent \"Build feature X\"\n#   claude-agent --model sonnet \"Quick task\"\n#   claude-agent --model opus \"Complex task\"\n#   claude-agent --workdir ~/project \"Build in this dir\"\n#\n# Skills available in session: /golden-horde, /horde-brainstorming,\n#   /horde-plan, /horde-implement, /horde-swarm, /horde-review,\n#   /horde-test, /horde-gate-testing, /horde-learn, /horde-skill-creator,\n#   /senior-architect, /senior-backend, /senior-frontend, /senior-devops,\n#   /senior-data-engineer, /senior-ml-engineer, /critical-reviewer,\n#   /code-reviewer, /brainstorming, and 70+ more\n\nset -eo pipefail\n\nCLAUDE_BIN=\"${CLAUDE_BIN:-/Users/kublai/.local/bin/claude}\"\nMODEL=\"opus\"\nWORKDIR=\"\"\nEXTRA_ARGS=()\n\n# Parse flags\nwhile [[ $# -gt 0 ]]; do\n    case \"$1\" in\n        --model)\n            MODEL=\"$2\"\n            shift 2\n            ;;\n        --budget)\n            # Accepted but ignored — no budget cap\n            shift 2\n            ;;\n        --workdir)\n            WORKDIR=\"$2\"\n            shift 2\n            ;;\n        --)\n            shift\n            break\n            ;;\n        --*)\n            EXTRA_ARGS+=(\"$1\")"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":5,"aggregated":"=== Claude Code wrapper ===\n#!/bin/bash\n# claude-agent: Wrapper for spawning Claude Code sessions from OpenClaw agents\n#\n# Handles:\n#   1. Strips CLAUDECODE env var (allows nested sessions)\n#   2. Adds --dangerously-skip-permissions (non-interactive)\n#   3. Uses default settings (all 23 plugins + 90+ skills)\n#   4. Configurable model\n#\n# Usage:\n#   claude-agent \"Build feature X\"\n#   claude-agent --model sonnet \"Quick task\"\n#   claude-agent --model opus \"Complex task\"\n#   claude-agent --workdir ~/project \"Build in this dir\"\n#\n# Skills available in session: /golden-horde, /horde-brainstorming,\n#   /horde-plan, /horde-implement, /horde-swarm, /horde-review,\n#   /horde-test, /horde-gate-testing, /horde-learn, /horde-skill-creator,\n#   /senior-architect, /senior-backend, /senior-frontend, /senior-devops,\n#   /senior-data-engineer, /senior-ml-engineer, /critical-reviewer,\n#   /code-reviewer, /brainstorming, and 70+ more\n\nset -eo pipefail\n\nCLAUDE_BIN=\"${CLAUDE_BIN:-/Users/kublai/.local/bin/claude}\"\nMODEL=\"opus\"\nWORKDIR=\"\"\nEXTRA_ARGS=()\n\n# Parse flags\nwhile [[ $# -gt 0 ]]; do\n    case \"$1\" in\n        --model)\n            MODEL=\"$2\"\n            shift 2\n            ;;\n        --budget)\n            # Accepted but ignored — no budget cap\n            shift 2\n            ;;\n        --workdir)\n            WORKDIR=\"$2\"\n            shift 2\n            ;;\n        --)\n            shift\n            break\n            ;;\n        --*)\n            EXTRA_ARGS+=(\"$1\")","cwd":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772751299971}}
