{"type":"message","id":"402cd9a6","parentId":"058f3334","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:55:10.796Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to know which files can be edited so that each agent prefers using horde skills by default when spawning Claude Code sessions.\n\nBased on what I found:\n\n1. **TOOLS.md** - Each agent has a TOOLS.md that already lists the horde skills available. I could add a preference instruction here.\n\n2. **AGENTS.md** - Each agent has an AGENTS.md that defines behavior. I could add a rule here.\n\n3. **agents.json** - Currently doesn't have a \"prompt\" or \"instructions\" field, but I could add one.\n\n4. **~/.claude/agents/** - There's an \"agents\" directory in the Claude config. Let me check if there are agent-specific settings there.\n\n5. **~/.claude/settings.json** - Global settings. I already know this has effortLevel and alwaysThinkingEnabled.\n\nThe best approach would be to:\n1. Add a \"defaultPrompt\" or \"systemPrompt\" field to agents.json that includes instructions to prefer horde skills\n2. Or update each agent's TOOLS.md to include a stronger preference for horde skills\n3. Or create agent-specific settings in ~/.claude/agents/\n\nLet me check the ~/.claude/agents/ directory to see if there are per-agent configs there.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check if there are agent-specific Claude configs and explore more options:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_86036c5166bd48b0ac7779ef","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== Claude agents directory ===\" && ls -la ~/.claude/agents/ 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1570ccf5fbca485ea05140a3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== Check for system prompt files ===\" && find ~/.openclaw/agents -name \"*.md\" -exec grep -l \"horde\\|skill\" {} \\; 2>/dev/null | head -10"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ebc7429db0504c37a14c5259","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== Check OpenC