{"type":"message","id":"491ab0df","parentId":"9aed8983","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:55:13.500Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ebc7429db0504c37a14c5259","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== Check OpenClaw agent config schema ===\n\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.2 (85377a2) — I'm not saying your workflow is chaotic... I'm just bringing a linter and a helmet.\n\nUsage: openclaw config [options] [command]\n\nNon-interactive config helpers (get/set/unset/file/validate). Run without\nsubcommand for the setup wizard.\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --section <section>  Configure wizard sections (repeatable). Use with no\n                       subcommand. (default: [])\n\nCommands:\n  file                 Print the active config file path\n  get                  Get a config value by dot path\n  set                  Set a config value by dot path\n  unset                Remove a config value by dot path\n  validate             Validate the current config against the schema without\n                       starting the gateway\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/config"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1436,"aggregated":"=== Check OpenClaw agent config schema ===\n\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.2 (85377a2) — I'm not saying your workflow is chaotic... I'm just bringing a linter and a helmet.\n\nUsage: openclaw config [options] [command]\n\nNon-interactive config helpers (get/set/unset/file/validate). Run without\nsubcommand for the setup wizard.\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --section <section>  Configure wizard sections (repeatable). Use with no\n                       subcommand. (default: [])\n\nCommands:\n  file                 Print the active config file path\n  get                  Get a config value by dot path\n  set                  Set a config value by dot path\n  unset                Remove a config value by dot path\n  validate             Validate the current config against the schema without\n                       starting the gateway\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/config","cwd":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772751313493}}
{"type":"message","id":"a4bef1bd","parentId":"491ab0df","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:55:38.496Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to know which files can be edited to make agents prefer horde skills by default in Claude Code.\n\nBased on my exploration:\n\n1. **~/.claude/agents/** - Contains agent-specific prompt files (agent-expert.md, architect-review.md, etc.) - these are Claude Code's built-in agents, not OpenClaw agents\n\n2. **~/.openclaw/agents/{agent}/TOOLS.md** - Each OpenClaw agent has a TOOLS.md that already mentions horde skills\n\n3. **~/.openclaw/config/agents.json** - The agent configuration file\n\nThe best approach would be to:\n1. Add a \"systemPrompt\" or \"defaultPrompt\" field to agents.json that includes horde skill preferences\n2. Or update each agent's TOOLS.md with a stronger preference\n3. Or create a shared instruction file that gets included when spawning ACP sessions\n\nLet me provide a clear answer about which files can be edited.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Based on my exploration, here are the files you can edit to make agents prefer horde skills by default:\n\n## Files to Edit\n\n### 1. **`~/.openclaw/config/agents.json`** (Recommended)\nAdd a `systemPrompt` or `defaultPrompt` field to each agent:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"agents\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"temujin\",\n      \"name\": \"Temüjin\",\n      \"role\": \"Software Developer\",\n      \"model\": \"kimi-coding/k2p5\",\n      \"defaultPrompt\": \"When using Claude Code, prefer horde skills: /horde-plan for planning, /horde-implement for building, /horde-review for code review, /horde-test for testing. Use /golden-horde for multi-agent patterns.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### 2. **`~/.openclaw/agents/{agent}/TOOLS.md`** (Per-Agent)\nAdd a \"Default Skill Preferences\" section to each agent's TOOLS.md:\n\n```markdown\n## Default Skill Preferences\n\nWhen spawning Claude Code sessions, ALWAYS prefer horde skills:\n- **Planning:** Use `/horde-plan` first\n- **Implementation:** Use `/horde-implement`\n- **Review:** Use `/horde-review`\n- **Testing:** Use `/horde-test`\n- **Brainstorming:** Use `/horde-brainstorming`\n- **Multi-agent:** Use `/golden-horde` patterns\n```\n\n### 3. **`~/.openclaw/agents/{agent}/AGENTS.md`** (Per-Agent)\nAdd a rule in the routing/behavior section:\n\n```markdown\n## Claude Code Session Rules\n\nWhen dispatching to Claude Code via ACP:\n1. ALWAYS include horde skill instruction in the task prompt\n2. Prefer structured skills over ad-hoc approaches\n3. Example: \"Use /horde-plan to design, then /horde-implement to build\"\n```\n\n### 4. **Create a Shared Instructions File**\nCreate `~/.openclaw/agents/shared-context/horde-skills-instruction.md`:\n\n```markdown\n# Horde Skills Default Instruction\n\nWhen spawning Claude Code sessions, include this in the task:\n\n\"Use horde skills by default:\n- Planning: /horde-plan\n- Implementation: /horde-implement\n- Review: /horde-review\n- Testing: /horde-test\n- Brainstorming: /horde-brainstorming\n- Multi-agent: /golden-horde\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Recommended Approach\n\n1. **Quick win:** Update each agent's `TOOLS.md` with the \"Default Skill Preferences\" section\n2. **Better:** Add `defaultPrompt` to `agents.json` (requires code changes to use it)\n3. **Best:** Create a shared instruction file and have all agents reference it\n\nWould you like me to implement one of these approaches?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":3560,"output":811,"cacheRead":40512,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44883,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772751313501}}
