{"type":"message","id":"eea8a24e","parentId":"79240565","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:57:55.817Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to create a more generalized file instead of just \"horde-skills-instruction.md\". They want a \"claude-instructions\" type file that all agents can reference when spawning Claude Code sessions.\n\nThis is a good idea - it would be more flexible and could include:\n1. Horde skills preferences\n2. General Claude Code best practices\n3. Effort/thinking settings\n4. Any other cross-agent instructions for ACP sessions\n\nLet me think about:\n1. Where to create this file (probably ~/.openclaw/agents/shared-context/)\n2. What to name it (claude-instructions.md or similar)\n3. What content to include\n4. How agents would reference it\n\nThe shared-context directory already exists based on what I've seen. Let me check what's in there and then propose a structure for this file.\n\nThe user wants to:\n1. Create a generalized claude-instructions.md file\n2. Have all agents reference it when spawning ACP sessions\n\nI should:\n1. Check the shared-context directory\n2. Propose a structure for the file\n3. Show how agents would reference it\n4. Optionally, create the file if they want","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Yes, that's a better approach. Let me check the shared-context directory and propose a generalized structure:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_80a1a1067c5e4563a30aff95","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== shared-context directory ===\" && ls -la ~/.openclaw/agents/main/shared-context/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"Directory not found\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1a6f23232a424f3d87e9c101","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== Check all shared-context dirs ===\" && find ~/.openclaw/agents -name \"shared-context\" -type d 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":7610,"output":349,"cacheRead":38080,