{"type":"message","id":"701ce4da","parentId":"99de1cd1","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:58:16.252Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I found the shared-context directories:\n1. /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/shared-context\n2. /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/shared-context\n\nThe main shared-context directory has several files already. I'll create the horde-skills-instruction.md file in this directory.\n\nLet me create the file with the default horde skill preferences.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Found the shared-context directory. Let me create the horde-skills-instruction.md file there:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cd5a7c9b8a1048bebdf10510","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/shared-context/HORDE-SKILLS-INSTRUCTION.md","content":"# Horde Skills Default Instruction\n\nWhen spawning Claude Code sessions via ACP, ALWAYS include this instruction in the task prompt:\n\n---\n\n## Default Horde Skills Instruction\n\n```\nUse horde skills by default for structured, high-quality work:\n\n**Planning & Design:**\n- Use `/horde-plan` for structured implementation plans with dependency tracking\n- Use `/horde-brainstorming` for ideation (diverge/evaluate/converge)\n\n**Implementation:**\n- Use `/horde-implement` to execute plans with quality checkpoints\n- Use `/golden-horde` for multi-agent patterns (review loop, debate, pipeline)\n\n**Quality Assurance:**\n- Use `/horde-review` for multi-domain critical review (security, perf, architecture)\n- Use `/horde-test` for parallel test suite execution\n- Use `/horde-gate-testing` for integration tests between phases\n\n**Specialist Skills:**\n- `/senior-architect` - System architecture\n- `/senior-backend` - Backend development\n- `/senior-frontend` - Frontend development\n- `/senior-devops` - DevOps/infrastructure\n- `/security-auditor` - Security review\n\n**Pattern:** Always prefer structured horde skills over ad-hoc approaches.\n```\n\n---\n\n## Usage in sessions_spawn\n\nInclude in your task prompt:\n\n```\nsessions_spawn({\n  task: \"<task description>\\n\\nUse horde skills: /horde-plan for planning, /horde-implement for building.\",\n  runtime: \"acp\",\n  agentId: \"claude\"\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n## Agent-Specific Defaults\n\n| Agent | Primary Skills |\n|-------|---------------|\n| Temujin (Dev) | `/horde-plan`, `/horde-implement`, `/horde-test` |\n| Mongke (Research) | `/horde-brainstorming`, `/horde-review` |\n| Chagatai (Content) | `/horde-brainstorming`, `/senior-architect` |\n| Jochi (Analysis) | `/horde-review`, `/horde-test` |\n| Ogedei (Ops) | `/senior-devops`, `/horde-implement` |\n| Kublai (Router) | `/golden-horde`, `/horde-plan` |\n\n---\n\n## Rationale\n\n1. **Consistency** - Structured skills produce consistent, high-quality output\n2. **Efficiency** - Pre-built patterns reduce cognitive load\n3. **Quality** - Built-in checkpoints catch issues early\n4. **Collaboration** - Multi-agent patterns enable complex workflows\n\n---\n\n*Created: 2026-03-05*\n*Last updated: 2026-03-05*\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":2587,"output":699,"cacheRead":44032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47318,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772751475915}}
