{"type":"message","id":"6b6143a4","parentId":"fec4ca0d","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:58:41.667Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if we can rename the file from \"horde-skills-instruction\" to a more generalized \"claude-instructions\" type file that all agents can reference.\n\nThis makes sense - instead of just horde skills, the file could include:\n1. Horde skills preferences (as I just created)\n2. General Claude Code session instructions\n3. Thinking/effort settings\n4. Any other cross-agent instructions for ACP sessions\n\nLet me update the file to be more generalized and rename it appropriately. I should:\n1. Rename the file to something like CLAUDE-CODE-INSTRUCTIONS.md or ACP-SESSION-INSTRUCTIONS.md\n2. Expand the content to include more than just horde skills\n3. Make it a comprehensive reference for all agents when spawning Claude Code sessions\n\nLet me create the generalized version.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Great idea. Let me rename and expand it to a generalized `CLAUDE-CODE-INSTRUCTIONS.md` file that covers all aspects of spawning Claude Code sessions:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ad9540cc24664afc80252717","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/shared-context/CLAUDE-CODE-INSTRUCTIONS.md","content":"# Claude Code Session Instructions\n\n**Reference for all Kurultai agents when spawning ACP sessions**\n\n---\n\n## Default Session Configuration\n\nAll Claude Code sessions inherit these settings from `~/.claude/settings.json`:\n- **Effort:** `high`\n- **Thinking:** `alwaysEnabled: true`\n- **Plugins:** 23 installed\n- **Skills:** 90+ available\n\n---\n\n## Horde Skills (Prefer by Default)\n\nWhen spawning Claude Code sessions via ACP, prefer structured horde skills:\n\n```\n**Planning & Design:**\n- `/horde-plan` - Structured implementation plans with dependency tracking\n- `/horde-brainstorming` - Ideation (diverge/evaluate/converge)\n\n**Implementation:**\n- `/horde-implement` - Execute plans with quality checkpoints\n- `/golden-horde` - Multi-agent patterns (review loop, debate, pipeline)\n\n**Quality Assurance:**\n- `/horde-review` - Multi-domain critical review (security, perf, architecture)\n- `/horde-test` - Parallel test suite execution\n- `/horde-gate-testing` - Integration tests between phases\n\n**Specialist Skills:**\n- `/senior-architect`, `/senior-backend`, `/senior-frontend`, `/senior-devops`\n- `/security-auditor`, `/code-reviewer`, `/critical-reviewer`\n```\n\n---\n\n## Session Spawn Template\n\n```javascript\nsessions_spawn({\n  task: `<task description>\n\nUse horde skills: /horde-plan for planning, /horde-implement for building.`,\n  runtime: \"acp\",\n  agentId: \"claude\",\n  mode: \"run\"  // or \"session\" for multi-turn\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n## Agent-Specific Defaults\n\n| Agent | Primary Skills | Use Case |\n|-------|---------------|----------|\n| Temujin (Dev) | `/horde-plan`, `/horde-implement`, `/horde-test` | Building features |\n| Mongke (Research) | `/horde-brainstorming`, `/horde-review` | Investigation |\n| Chagatai (Content) | `/horde-brainstorming`, `/senior-architect` | Writing, docs |\n| Jochi (Analysis) | `/horde-review`, `/horde-test` | Data analysis |\n| Ogedei (Ops) | `/senior-devops`, `/horde-implement` | Infrastructure |\n| Kublai (Router) | `/golden-horde`, `/horde-plan` | Coordination |\n\n---\n\n## Best Practices\n\n### 1. Always Include Skill Instruction\nInclude horde skill preference in every task prompt:\n```\n\"Use /horde-plan to design, then /horde-implement to build\"\n```\n\n### 2. Choose the Right Mode\n- `mode: \"run\"` - One-shot tasks (most common)\n- `mode: \"session\"` - Multi-turn work with thread persistence\n\n### 3. Set Appropriate Timeout\n- Simple tasks: default timeout\n- Complex builds: `runTimeoutSeconds: 600` (10 min)\n- Investigation: `runTimeoutSeconds: 1800` (30 min)\n\n### 4. Provide Context\nInclude relevant file paths, URLs, and requirements in the task:\n```\nBuild feature X in /Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/\nReference: SPEC.md at line 50-100\nDeploy to Railway project: parsethe.media\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Locations\n\n| Resource | Path |\n|----------|------|\n| Claude settings | `~/.claude/settings.json` |\n| Claude skills | `~/.codex/skills/` |\n| Claude wrapper | `~/.local/bin/claude-agent` |\n| This file | `~/.openclaw/agents/main/shared-context/CLAUDE-CODE-INSTRUCTIONS.md` |\n\n---\n\n## Related Documentation\n\n- `TOOLS.md` - Agent-specific tool usage\n- `AGENTS.md` - Agent routing and behavior\n- `~/.claude/README.md` - Claude Code documentation\n\n---\n\n*Created: 2026-03-05*\n*Last updated: 2026-03-05*\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":1719,"output":1108,"cacheRead":45632,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48459,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772751496282}}
