{"type":"message","id":"d85b180d","parentId":"683e3c52","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:15:39.887Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! The 4 skills have been copied to ~/.codex/skills/. Now I need to:\n\n1. Create CLAUDE.md files for each agent to reference these skills\n2. The agents are: kublai (main), temujin, mongke, chagatai, jochi, ogedei\n\nBut wait - I need to think about what \"claude.md\" means. The user mentioned updating each agent's \"claude.md\" to be able to use these skills.\n\nLooking at the agent directories, I don't think there's a CLAUDE.md file. The agents have:\n- AGENTS.md\n- TOOLS.md\n- SOUL.md\n- IDENTITY.md\n- MEMORY.md\n\nMaybe the user wants me to create a CLAUDE.md file for each agent? Or maybe they want me to update an existing file?\n\nLet me check what files exist in each agent's directory.\n\nActually, I think the user wants me to create a CLAUDE.md file that instructs the agent on how to use Claude Code with these skills. This would be similar to the TOOLS.md but specifically for Claude Code sessions.\n\nLet me create a CLAUDE.md file for each agent that references the installed skills and provides guidance on how to use them.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"All 4 skills are now installed. Let me check the agent directories and create CLAUDE.md files for each agent:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1d01d6ef740c47fd979286ed","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== Check agent directories ===\" && for agent in main temujin mongke chagatai jochi ogedei; do\n  echo \"--- $agent ---\"\n  ls ~/.openclaw/agents/$agent/*.md 2>/dev/null | head -10 || echo \"No .md files\"\ndone"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":71842,"output":368,"cacheRead":1600,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73810,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772756125281}}
