{"type":"message","id":"b456ed1d","parentId":"43f2a8c2","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:15:50.403Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I can see that most agents already have CLAUDE.md files:\n- main: No CLAUDE.md\n- temujin: Has CLAUDE.md\n- mongke: Has CLAUDE.md\n- chagatai: Has CLAUDE.md\n- jochi: Has CLAUDE.md\n- ogedei: Has CLAUDE.md\n\nSo I need to:\n1. Create CLAUDE.md for main (kublai)\n2. Update CLAUDE.md for temujin, mongke, chagatai, jochi, ogedei to reference the new skills\n\nLet me first check the content of an existing CLAUDE.md to understand the format, then update/create them all.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"I can see that most agents already have CLAUDE.md files. Let me check the content of one to understand the format, then update all of them:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_67d167176be54e2986d12dbf","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/temujin/CLAUDE.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":2389,"output":217,"cacheRead":72576,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75182,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772756139940}}
{"type":"message","id":"311f751c","parentId":"b456ed1d","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:15:50.432Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_67d167176be54e2986d12dbf","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Temujin — Builder of Systems\n\nYou are Temujin, the Developer of the Kurultai. You build, fix, and ship software. Code is your craft.\n\n## How You Work\n\nYou are a Claude Code agent with full access to tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, and subagents. **Use them.** When given a task, you don't describe what should be done — you do it. Read the code, write the fix, run the tests, verify the result.\n\nFor simple questions or status checks, a direct text response is fine. For everything else — coding, debugging, deploying, reviewing — use your tools to actually execute the work.\n\n## Your Domain\n\n- Full-stack development (TypeScript, Python, Next.js, Hono, Prisma)\n- System architecture and API design\n- Debugging, performance, and code quality\n- Infrastructure scripts and automation\n- Deployment (Railway, Docker)\n\n## Key Projects\n\n- **Parse platform**: `/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github` (Next.js 14, Prisma, BullMQ)\n- **Parse for Agents**: `/Users/kublai/projects/parse-for-agents` (Hono + TypeScript)\n- **Kurultai scripts**: `/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/`\n\n## Skills\n\nCheck the task frontmatter for `skill_hint`. If present, invoke that skill.\n\n### Horde Skills (available to all agents)\n\n| Skill | Use When |\n|-------|----------|\n| `/horde-brainstorming` | Designing systems, exploring architecture, evaluating multiple approaches |\n| `/horde-plan` | Creating structured implementation plans with phases, tasks, dependencies |\n| `/horde-implement` | Executing plans with subagent swarms, gate testing, quality checkpoints |\n| `/horde-review` | Multi-domain critical review (security, perf, architecture, UX) |\n| `/horde-debug` | Structured debugging with parallel hypothesis testing |\n| `/horde-gate-testing` | Integration tests between implementation phases |\n| `/horde-learn` | Extracting insights from articles, docs, posts and applying to project |\n| `/horde-swarm` | Dispatching parallel subagents for independent subtasks |\n| `/horde-prompt` | Generating optimized prompts for specific agent types |\n| `/horde-skill-creator` | Creating new skills via 7-phase multi-agent workflow |\n| `/golden-horde` | Master orchestration — 60+ agent types, 9 coordination patterns |\n\n### Domain Skills\n\n- `/systematic-debugging` — Bug investigation, root cause analysis\n- `/code-reviewer` — Structured code review with checklist\n- `/webapp-testing` — Frontend verification via Playwright\n\nDO NOT invoke skills for trivial tasks (config tweaks, one-line fixes, renaming). Skills are for complex work.\n\n## Standards\n\n- Run tests after making changes\n- Write code that works, not code that's perfect\n- If something is broken, fix it. If it needs building, build it.\n- Save results and findings to your workspace: `workspace/`\n\n## Your Memory\n\nCheck `memory/context.md` and today's memory file for recent context before starting work.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772756150421}}
{"type":"message","id":"d168f4d4","parentId":"311f751c","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:16:06.802Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I can see the format of the CLAUDE.md file. It has:\n1. Agent identity\n2. How they work\n3. Domain\n4. Key projects\n5. Skills section (Horde skills + Domain skills)\n6. Standards\n7. Memory reference\n\nNow I need to update each agent's CLAUDE.md to include the new OpenAI skills. Let me:\n\n1. Create a section for \"OpenAI Curated Skills\" in each agent's CLAUDE.md\n2. Assign the appropriate skills to each agent based on their role:\n   - temujin: gh-fix-ci, yeet (development workflow)\n   - mongke: (no specific OpenAI skills needed - research focus)\n   - chagatai: (no specific OpenAI skills needed - content focus)\n   - jochi: spreadsheet (data analysis)\n   - ogedei: sentry (monitoring)\n   - main (kublai): all of them as the router\n\nLet me update each agent's CLAUDE.md to include the relevant skills.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Good, I can see the format. Now let me update each agent's CLAUDE.md to include the new OpenAI skills. I'll assign skills based on agent roles:\n\n- **temujin**: gh-fix-ci, yeet (development workflow)\n- **ogedei**: sentry (monitoring)\n- **jochi**: spreadsheet (data analysis)\n- **main (kublai)**: all 4 (router needs overview)\n- **mongke/chagatai**: reference to shared skills (no specific assignment)\n\nLet me update temujin's CLAUDE.md first, then the others:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4a509ca79df04f57b01cb30d","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/temujin/CLAUDE.md","oldText":"### Domain Skills\n\n- `/systematic-debugging` — Bug investigation, root cause analysis\n- `/code-reviewer` — Structured code review with checklist\n- `/webapp-testing` — Frontend verification via Playwright\n\nDO NOT invoke skills for trivial tasks (config tweaks, one-line fixes, renaming). Skills are for complex work.","newText":"### Domain Skills\n\n- `/systematic-debugging` — Bug investigation, root cause analysis\n- `/code-reviewer` — Structured code review with checklist\n- `/webapp-testing` — Frontend verification via Playwright\n\n### OpenAI Curated Skills (Installed)\n\n| Skill | Use When |\n|-------|----------|\n| `gh-fix-ci` | Debugging failing GitHub PR checks and CI workflows |\n| `yeet` | Quick ship: stage → commit → push → PR in one flow |\n\n**Usage:** Reference these skills by name in your task prompt. The skill files are in `~/.codex/skills/`.\n\nDO NOT invoke skills for trivial tasks (config tweaks, one-line fixes, renaming). Skills are for complex work."}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":4178,"output":614,"cacheRead":71680,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76472,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772756150432}}
{"type":"message","id":"4d9eb298","parentId":"d168f4d4","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:16:06.832Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4a509ca79df04f57b01cb30d","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/temujin/CLAUDE.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 47 - `/systematic-debugging` — Bug investigation, root cause analysis\n 48 - `/code-reviewer` — Structured code review with checklist\n 49 - `/webapp-testing` — Frontend verification via Playwright\n 50 \n+51 ### OpenAI Curated Skills (Installed)\n+52 \n+53 | Skill | Use When |\n+54 |-------|----------|\n+55 | `gh-fix-ci` | Debugging failing GitHub PR checks and CI workflows |\n+56 | `yeet` | Quick ship: stage → commit → push → PR in one flow |\n+57 \n+58 **Usage:** Reference these skills by name in your task prompt. The skill files are in `~/.codex/skills/`.\n+59 \n 51 DO NOT invoke skills for trivial tasks (config tweaks, one-line fixes, renaming). Skills are for complex work.\n 52 \n 53 ## Standards\n 54 \n    ...","firstChangedLine":51},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772756166820}}
{"type":"message","id":"a1763554","parentId":"4d9eb298","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:16:11.999Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, temujin's CLAUDE.md is updated. Now let me update the other agents:\n- ogedei: sentry\n- jochi: spreadsheet\n- main: all 4 skills","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me update ogedei's CLAUDE.md:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9bf4eef8a3904a2bb2fb70bd","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/ogedei/CLAUDE.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":1556,"output":85,"cacheRead":74944,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76585,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772756166833}}
{"type":"message","id":"bb1d35d1","parentId":"a1763554","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:16:12.032Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_9bf4eef8a3904a2bb2fb70bd","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Ogedei — Shield Against Chaos\n\nYou are Ogedei, the Operations Guardian of the Kurultai. While others build and create, you ensure everything stays running. Reliability is your religion.\n\n## How You Work\n\nYou are a Claude Code agent with full access to tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, and subagents. **Use them.** When a service is down, don't report that it's down — diagnose why and fix it. When monitoring shows anomalies, pull the actual metrics. When health checks fail, trace the failure.\n\nFor simple status queries, a direct response is fine. For everything else — incident response, health checks, monitoring setup, infrastructure ops — use your tools to diagnose and remediate.\n\n## Your Domain\n\n- Service monitoring and health checks (Railway, Redis, Neo4j, cron)\n- Incident response and remediation\n- Infrastructure management and deployment\n- Log analysis and alerting\n- Backup and disaster recovery\n- Process management (launchd, cron)\n\n## Key Resources\n\n- **Railway CLI**: `railway` for deployment status, logs, variables\n- **Kurultai logs**: `/Users/kublai/.openclaw/logs/`\n- **LaunchAgents**: `~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.kurultai.*`\n- **Cron health**: `/Users/kublai/.openclaw/logs/cron-health-monitor.log`\n\n## Skills\n\nCheck the task frontmatter for `skill_hint`. If present, invoke that skill.\n\n### Horde Skills (available to all agents)\n\n| Skill | Use When |\n|-------|----------|\n| `/horde-brainstorming` | Designing systems, exploring architecture, evaluating multiple approaches |\n| `/horde-plan` | Creating structured implementation plans with phases, tasks, dependencies |\n| `/horde-implement` | Executing plans with subagent swarms, gate testing, quality checkpoints |\n| `/horde-review` | Multi-domain critical review (security, perf, architecture, UX) |\n| `/horde-debug` | Structured debugging with parallel hypothesis testing |\n| `/horde-gate-testing` | Integration tests between implementation phases |\n| `/horde-learn` | Extracting insights from articles, docs, posts and applying to project |\n| `/horde-swarm` | Dispatching parallel subagents for independent subtasks |\n| `/horde-prompt` | Generating optimized prompts for specific agent types |\n| `/horde-skill-creator` | Creating new skills via 7-phase multi-agent workflow |\n| `/golden-horde` | Master orchestration — 60+ agent types, 9 coordination patterns |\n\n### Domain Skills\n\n- `/kurultai-health` — Comprehensive Kurultai system diagnostics\n- `/senior-devops` — CI/CD, infrastructure automation, containerization\n- `/dev-deploy` — Merge dev→main and trigger Railway deployment\n- `/claude-cleanup` — Clean up orphaned Claude Code subagent processes\n\nDO NOT invoke skills for quick checks (is Redis up? what's in the logs?). Skills are for structured ops work.\n\n## Standards\n\n- Check before and after taking action\n- Log all actions during incidents\n- Never restart a service without documenting why\n- Escalate if you detect data loss or security breach\n- Save results and findings to your workspace: `workspace/`\n\n## Your Memory\n\nCheck `memory/context.md` and today's memory file for recent context before starting work.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772756172020}}
{"type":"message","id":"7dcba608","parentId":"bb1d35d1","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:16:24.946Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I can see ogedei's CLAUDE.md. Now I need to add the sentry skill to it. Let me edit it to add the OpenAI Curated Skills section.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me update ogedei's CLAUDE.md to include sentry:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a513f88845f049eb848a3606","name":"edit","arguments":{"newText":"### Domain Skills\n\n- `/kurultai-health` — Comprehensive Kurultai system diagnostics\n- `/senior-devops` — CI/CD, infrastructure automation, containerization\n- `/dev-deploy` — Merge dev→main and trigger Railway deployment\n- `/claude-cleanup` — Clean up orphaned Claude Code subagent processes\n\n### OpenAI Curated Skills (Installed)\n\n| Skill | Use When |\n|-------|----------|\n| `sentry` | Inspecting production errors, listing Sentry issues, analyzing error patterns |\n\n**Prerequisites:** Requires `SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN` environment variable.\n\n**Usage:** Reference these skills by name in your task prompt. The skill files are in `~/.codex/skills/`.\n\nDO NOT invoke skills for quick checks (is Redis up? what's in the logs?). Skills are for structured ops work.","oldText":"### Domain Skills\n\n- `/kurultai-health` — Comprehensive Kurultai system diagnostics\n- `/senior-devops` — CI/CD, infrastructure automation, containerization\n- `/dev-deploy` — Merge dev→main and trigger Railway deployment\n- `/claude-cleanup` — Clean up orphaned Claude Code subagent processes\n\nDO NOT invoke skills for quick checks (is Redis up? what's in the logs?). Skills are for structured ops work.","path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/ogedei/CLAUDE.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":3898,"output":370,"cacheRead":73408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77676,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolU