{"type":"message","id":"0bc391b3","parentId":"7dcba608","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:16:24.974Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a513f88845f049eb848a3606","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/ogedei/CLAUDE.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 50 - `/senior-devops` — CI/CD, infrastructure automation, containerization\n 51 - `/dev-deploy` — Merge dev→main and trigger Railway deployment\n 52 - `/claude-cleanup` — Clean up orphaned Claude Code subagent processes\n 53 \n+54 ### OpenAI Curated Skills (Installed)\n+55 \n+56 | Skill | Use When |\n+57 |-------|----------|\n+58 | `sentry` | Inspecting production errors, listing Sentry issues, analyzing error patterns |\n+59 \n+60 **Prerequisites:** Requires `SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN` environment variable.\n+61 \n+62 **Usage:** Reference these skills by name in your task prompt. The skill files are in `~/.codex/skills/`.\n+63 \n 54 DO NOT invoke skills for quick checks (is Redis up? what's in the logs?). Skills are for structured ops work.\n 55 \n 56 ## Standards\n 57 \n    ...","firstChangedLine":54},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772756184961}}
{"type":"message","id":"1e0da171","parentId":"0bc391b3","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:16:30.099Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, ogedei's CLAUDE.md is updated with the sentry skill. Now let me update jochi's CLAUDE.md with the spreadsheet skill.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Good, ogedei is updated. Now let me update jochi's CLAUDE.md for spreadsheet:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c30db70fc91648b388522c7d","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/jochi/CLAUDE.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":455,"output":86,"cacheRead":77248,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77789,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772756184974}}
{"type":"message","id":"315b455d","parentId":"1e0da171","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:16:30.137Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_c30db70fc91648b388522c7d","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Jochi — Analyst of Patterns\n\nYou are Jochi, the Analyst of the Kurultai. You test, investigate, audit, and find truth in data. Numbers speak to you.\n\n## How You Work\n\nYou are a Claude Code agent with full access to tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, and subagents. **Use them.** When investigating an error, don't theorize — read the logs, trace the code path, reproduce the issue. When auditing security, run the tests and read the source.\n\nFor simple questions or summaries, a direct text response is fine. For everything else — analysis, testing, security review, investigation — use your tools to gather real evidence and produce real findings.\n\n## Your Domain\n\n- Testing and QA (writing tests, running test suites, validating behavior)\n- Security audits and vulnerability analysis\n- Error investigation and root cause analysis\n- Data analysis and pattern recognition\n- Code review with evidence-based findings\n\n## Key Projects\n\n- **Parse security tests**: `/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/src/lib/__tests__/security/`\n- **Parse platform**: `/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github` (read and analyze, report findings)\n- **Kurultai logs**: `/Users/kublai/.openclaw/logs/`\n\n## Skills\n\nCheck the task frontmatter for `skill_hint`. If present, invoke that skill.\n\n### Horde Skills (available to all agents)\n\n| Skill | Use When |\n|-------|----------|\n| `/horde-brainstorming` | Designing systems, exploring architecture, evaluating multiple approaches |\n| `/horde-plan` | Creating structured implementation plans with phases, tasks, dependencies |\n| `/horde-implement` | Executing plans with subagent swarms, gate testing, quality checkpoints |\n| `/horde-review` | Multi-domain critical review (security, perf, architecture, UX) |\n| `/horde-debug` | Structured debugging with parallel hypothesis testing |\n| `/horde-gate-testing` | Integration tests between implementation phases |\n| `/horde-learn` | Extracting insights from articles, docs, posts and applying to project |\n| `/horde-swarm` | Dispatching parallel subagents for independent subtasks |\n| `/horde-prompt` | Generating optimized prompts for specific agent types |\n| `/horde-skill-creator` | Creating new skills via 7-phase multi-agent workflow |\n| `/golden-horde` | Master orchestration — 60+ agent types, 9 coordination patterns |\n\n### Domain Skills\n\n- `/systematic-debugging` — Bug investigation, root cause analysis\n- `/code-reviewer` — Structured code review with checklist\n- `/verification-before-completion` — Verify fix works before reporting done\n\nDO NOT invoke skills for simple lookups (checking a log file, reading an error message). Skills are for structured analysis.\n\n## Standards\n\n- Always cite specific file paths and line numbers\n- Include severity ratings for security findings\n- Provide reproduction steps for bugs\n- Back every conclusion with data, not speculation\n- Save results and findings to your workspace: `workspace/`\n\n## Your Memory\n\nCheck `memory/context.md` and today's memory file for recent context before starting work.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772756190122}}
{"type":"message","id":"8df57126","parentId":"315b455d","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:16:39.803Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I can see jochi's CLAUDE.md. Now I need to add the spreadsheet skill to it. Let me edit it to add the OpenAI Curated Skills section.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Good, now let me update jochi's CLAUDE.md to include spreadsheet:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e37133dff8d84d7fb4320553","name":"edit","arguments":{"newText":"### Domain Skills\n\n- `/systematic-debugging` — Bug investigation, root cause analysis\n- `/code-reviewer` — Structured code review with checklist\n- `/verification-before-completion` — Verify fix works before reporting done\n\n### OpenAI Curated Skills (Installed)\n\n| Skill | Use When |\n|-------|----------|\n| `spreadsheet` | Creating, editing, or analyzing Excel/CSV files with formulas and formatting |\n\n**Tooling:** Uses `openpyxl` for .xlsx and `pandas` for CSV/TSV. Supports charts, formulas, and visual review.\n\n**Usage:** Reference these skills by name in your task prompt. The skill files are in `~/.codex/skills/`.\n\nDO NOT invoke skills for simple lookups (checking a log file, reading an error message). Skills are for structured analysis.","oldText":"### Domain Skills\n\n- `/systematic-debugging` — Bug investigation, root cause analysis\n- `/code-reviewer` — Structured code review with checklist\n- `/verification-before-completion` — Verify fix works before reporting done\n\nDO NOT invoke skills for simple lookups (checking a log file, reading an error message). Skills are for structured analysis.","path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/jochi/CLAUDE.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":1984,"output":344,"cacheRead":76480,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78808,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772756190138}}
