{"type":"message","id":"874271e9","parentId":"50977787","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:29:11.597Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to classify a task and state which agent I would route it to, WITHOUT executing or delegating. This is a routing test.\n\nLet me analyze the prompt: \"Research known prompt injection techniques and test our API against them\"\n\nThis is a combination task:\n1. Research prompt injection techniques - research task\n2. Test our API against them - security testing/QA task\n\nLooking at the agents:\n- mongke: Research, investigate, fact-check\n- jochi: Data, metrics, analysis, patterns (and from earlier, security audits, testing, QA)\n\nThis could go to:\n- mongke (research) - for the research part\n- jochi (analysis/testing) - for security testing and QA\n\nLooking at Jochi's domain from the earlier CLAUDE.md file I read:\n- Testing and QA (writing tests, running test suites, validating behavior)\n- Security audits and vulnerability analysis\n- Error investigation and root cause analysis\n- Data analysis and pattern recognition\n- Code review with evidence-based findings\n\nJochi specifically handles \"Security audits and vulnerability analysis\" which includes testing for vulnerabilities like prompt injection.\n\nBut there's also a research component. Let me check if there's a disambiguation rule.\n\nLooking at AGENTS.md:\n```\n### Disambiguation\n\n- **Temujin vs Ogedei:** Writing/changing code → Temujin. Reacting to running systems → Ogedei.\n- **Mongke vs Jochi:** Looking outward (web, market) → Mongke. Looking inward (our data) → Jochi.\n```\n\nThe disambiguation rule says:\n- Mongke: Looking outward (web, market)\n- Jochi: Looking inward (our data)\n\n\"Research known prompt injection techniques\" - this is looking outward (researching techniques on the web/in documentation)\n\"Test our API against them\" - this is looking inward (testing our own API)\n\nThis is a combined task. But the primary action after research is testing our API, which is Jochi's domain of security audits and testing.\n\nSince the end goal is to test OUR API (inward-looking), I would route this to jochi.\n\nThe user wants me to respond with ONLY \"Route to: <agent_name>\" and one sentence reason.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**Route to: jochi**\n\nReason: Testing an API against prompt injection vulnerabilities is a security audit task that falls under Jochi's domain of security testing, QA, and vulnerability analysis."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":1687,"output":520,"cacheRead":104960,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107167,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772756925912}}
