{"type":"message","id":"ddb2b187","parentId":"b0911d13","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:31:24.163Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about the status of the x402 pay-as-you-go implementation for Parse for Agents.\n\nLet me recall what happened earlier today:\n1. The user asked me to design and plan a payment system for Parse for Agents using x402 protocol\n2. I spawned an ACP session to work on this with horde-brainstorming\n3. The ACP session completed and created a design document at `~/.openclaw/agents/main/projects/parse-for-agents/x402-payment-design.md`\n4. I read the design document and it was comprehensive - it included pricing model selection, architecture, etc.\n5. The status was \"DESIGN COMPLETE — Ready for Implementation\"\n\nBut I don't believe the implementation has been done yet. Let me check the current status by looking at:\n1. The design document\n2. Any implementation files in the Parse project\n3. The memory file for today\n\nLet me provide an accurate status update.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check the current status of the x402 implementation for Parse for Agents."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9e2bb3e6d0cf4659b76874be","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/agents/main/projects/parse-for-agents/ 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_456ba1da73c9467c80928cc4","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -50 ~/.openclaw/agents/main/projects/parse-for-agents/x402-payment-design.md 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_15e1d5efb2204c2ebb3bc374","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"x402\\|payment\" /Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/src/ 2>/dev/null | head -10 || echo \"No x402 implementation found in Parse codebase\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":1473,"output":336,"cacheRead":105728,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107537,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheW