{"type":"message","id":"da3ca672","parentId":"c61962d6","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:11:34.208Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Hourly Kurultai Reflection - 8:02 PM EST\n\n## Summary\n\n**System Grade: D**\n\n**Critical Discovery:** The execution loop is broken. Tasks ARE being created (5 tasks at 7:10 PM) but agents are NOT executing them. All 5 tasks have been stuck in `.executing` state for 55+ minutes.\n\n**Key Metrics:**\n- Fleet utilization: **~5%** (95% waste)\n- Tasks completed this hour: **0**\n- Stalled tasks: **5** (all agents)\n- System: Neo4j UP, Redis UP, Gateway DOWN (4444)\n\n## Agent Grades\n\n| Agent | Grade | Status |\n|-------|-------|--------|\n| Temujin | F | Stalled, sandbox blocked (but MVP reportedly done externally) |\n| Mongke | F | Claimed no task assigned, but task file exists |\n| Chagatai | D | Claimed file missing, but file verified to exist |\n| Jochi | D | Delivered 95% fleet waste analysis inline |\n| Ogedei | C | Watchdog fix confirmed in code |\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe task-watcher daemon IS running (PID 29632, 10-sec poll) but dispatched tasks are not being executed by agents. This is an **execution gap**, not a dispatch problem - task files exist but agents don't pick them up.\n\n## Actions Needed\n\n1. **CRITICAL:** Fix execution loop - investigate why task-watcher doesn't trigger agent execution\n2. Reset 5 stalled tasks to pending state\n3. Restart task-watcher daemon if needed\n4. Verify Gateway (port 4444 down)\n\n## Positive Finding\n\nOgedei's watchdog false-positive fix IS confirmed in code (line 141 of ogedei-watchdog.py has correct conditions).\n\nReport saved to: `logs/reflections/2026-03-05-2002-hourly-reflection.md`"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772759494208}}
